1
00:00:07,560 --> 00:00:09,804
[Day 4 of the trip, morning]
Come on, just give me this one today.

2
00:00:09,804 --> 00:00:12,803
We're about to do the third benefit draw here.

3
00:00:12,803 --> 00:00:14,159
I never want to see this again, seriously.

4
00:00:14,159 --> 00:00:16,259
[Time to escape the two-phone swamp...]
For real.

5
00:00:16,259 --> 00:00:18,660
[Got one!]
Seo Jun!

6
00:00:18,660 --> 00:00:21,103
[Won the lodging]
This works.

7
00:00:21,103 --> 00:00:23,224
There was something
I really had my heart set on, though.

8
00:00:23,224 --> 00:00:25,793
I was sure a car would come up.

9
00:00:25,793 --> 00:00:28,904
Or could we honestly
pull off a day trip to Jeju?

10
00:00:28,904 --> 00:00:30,924
There's a way from Gwangju. Gwangju Airport.

11
00:00:30,924 --> 00:00:31,903
I'm in.

12
00:00:31,903 --> 00:00:34,304
Excuse me, can we still grab tickets right now?

13
00:00:34,304 --> 00:00:36,796
There aren't any seats left for today...

14
00:00:36,796 --> 00:00:38,331
- Oh, is that right?
- Yes.

15
00:00:38,331 --> 00:00:40,893
[The Jeju obsession carries
right on into the lodging...]

16
00:00:40,893 --> 00:00:43,493
[Hunting next-day flights right away]
Gwangju, Jeju.

17
00:00:43,493 --> 00:00:44,704
These are way too pricey, though.

18
00:00:44,704 --> 00:00:46,172
We could just take a boat over.

19
00:00:46,172 --> 00:00:48,241
[Mokpo to Jeju]
[Departs 1 AM]

20
00:00:48,241 --> 00:00:49,842
We'd have to head out later tonight.

21
00:00:49,842 --> 00:00:51,872
[Getting to Jeju is no easy feat...]
Even then it won't work.

22
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,947
[Results of the 1.5-Hour Jeju Debate]
If only we'd gone on day one.

23
00:00:54,947 --> 00:00:56,949
[Plan A. 2/28, From Gwangju to Jeju]
We should've gone day one and come back.

24
00:00:56,949 --> 00:00:59,043
[Every Jeju plan falls through]

25
00:00:59,043 --> 00:01:01,254
I'm starving over here.

26
00:01:01,254 --> 00:01:03,088
[Let's eat first, then deal with it.]
Let's hit Hanwoo*.

27
00:01:03,956 --> 00:01:07,463
[Hitting the laundromat before dinner]

28
00:01:07,463 --> 00:01:10,004
- So we hit the nearest laundromat first.
- Right.

29
00:01:10,004 --> 00:01:12,632
Then on to the Hanwoo* main branch!

30
00:01:12,632 --> 00:01:14,485
This is the spot. Self-service laundromat.

31
00:01:14,485 --> 00:01:15,868
- It's right out front!
- It's literally right there.

32
00:01:15,868 --> 00:01:17,570
What are we even doing?

33
00:01:17,570 --> 00:01:18,971
[The laundromat was right next door!]

34
00:01:18,971 --> 00:01:21,674
[6:20 PM, Self-service laundromat]

35
00:01:21,674 --> 00:01:23,738
[Tossing the laundry all in]

36
00:01:23,738 --> 00:01:25,645
Standard wash.

37
00:01:25,645 --> 00:01:27,280
That's 4,000 won.

38
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:31,535
[Expense log, wash: -4,000 won,
balance: 223,310 won]

39
00:01:31,535 --> 00:01:33,185
Let's dry these back at the place.

40
00:01:33,185 --> 00:01:35,554
- Yeah, drying at the place is fine.
- Sure.

41
00:01:36,822 --> 00:01:38,024
35 minutes?

42
00:01:38,024 --> 00:01:39,856
[The wash takes about 35 minutes]
35 minutes?

43
00:01:39,856 --> 00:01:41,360
Okay, so now then...

44
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:44,736
- There's an arcade machine here too.
- It's so you can game while you wait.

45
00:01:45,464 --> 00:01:46,399
One round?

46
00:01:46,399 --> 00:01:48,026
Let's do a round.

47
00:01:48,026 --> 00:01:49,992
35 minutes will fly by.

48
00:01:49,992 --> 00:01:51,760
Oh, this isn't free?

49
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,316
[Sadly, it's a paid service]
It wouldn't be free.

50
00:01:53,316 --> 00:01:55,908
I picked something up, that's right.

51
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:58,911
[Eureka]

52
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:01,660
[As for this very coin]

53
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:04,016
[On the subway to the lodging today]
Where did we see this round thing?

54
00:02:04,016 --> 00:02:06,953
Huh? A 500-won coin?

55
00:02:06,953 --> 00:02:08,187
Is this thing real?

56
00:02:08,187 --> 00:02:11,490
[Finding a 500-won coin with insane luck]

57
00:02:11,490 --> 00:02:14,193
[Who knew that coin
would come in handy so fast...]

58
00:02:14,193 --> 00:02:16,696
[Expense log, arcade machine: -500 won,
Balance: 222,810 won]

59
00:02:16,696 --> 00:02:18,598
Let's head out.

60
00:02:18,598 --> 00:02:20,393
- Looks like the time is up?
- Just looking at this makes me feel clean.

61
00:02:20,393 --> 00:02:21,860
- All finished.
- Time's completely up.

62
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,803
- Let's get going.
- Yeah.

63
00:02:23,803 --> 00:02:24,828
[Tossing the laundry
over a rack back into the room]

64
00:02:24,828 --> 00:02:26,572
- Dropped it all off.
- Yeah.

65
00:02:26,572 --> 00:02:27,673
Right.

66
00:02:27,673 --> 00:02:29,108
- That was a quick trip.
- Yeah.

67
00:02:29,108 --> 00:02:30,082
[Finally off to the dinner spot!]

68
00:02:30,082 --> 00:02:33,012
Honestly though, this is what
I've been dying to eat today.

69
00:02:33,012 --> 00:02:35,282
[Woo Shik, waiting for raw beef since day one]

70
00:02:35,282 --> 00:02:36,463
How do we get there from here?

71
00:02:36,463 --> 00:02:39,862
We cross to the other side
and head down a bit more.

72
00:02:39,862 --> 00:02:42,555
- Should we try taking a left into this alley?
- Yeah.

73
00:02:42,555 --> 00:02:44,673
[Treasurer Park knowing the streets as always]

74
00:02:44,673 --> 00:02:48,027
- Checking out this neighborhood is nice.
- Yeah.

75
00:02:48,027 --> 00:02:49,362
[A peaceful walk to the restaurant]

76
00:02:49,362 --> 00:02:50,696
It's insanely quiet here.

77
00:02:50,696 --> 00:02:51,864
Pretty sure it's to the right.

78
00:02:51,864 --> 00:02:52,832
[About 15 minutes into the walk]

79
00:02:52,832 --> 00:02:54,154
Do we take a right or a left?

80
00:02:54,154 --> 00:02:56,668
- I vote right.
- My money's on left.

81
00:02:57,668 --> 00:02:59,860
- Better off just asking someone.
- Huh?

82
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:02,375
[Park hits a wall]
- Not this way? - Let's ask.

83
00:03:02,375 --> 00:03:03,709
[Stepping into the convenience store]

84
00:03:03,709 --> 00:03:05,134
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

85
00:03:05,134 --> 00:03:06,893
Do you know where Hanwoo* is?

86
00:03:06,893 --> 00:03:09,359
Just left of the K* building here...

87
00:03:09,359 --> 00:03:10,716
So down that alley...

88
00:03:10,716 --> 00:03:12,285
Thanks a lot.

89
00:03:12,285 --> 00:03:13,386
- Thanks.
- Appreciate it.

90
00:03:13,386 --> 00:03:14,320
[Asking for directions is a breeze now]

91
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,162
[Over there?] [Yes!]

92
00:03:16,162 --> 00:03:18,224
- Toward the K* building.
- Towards K*.

93
00:03:18,224 --> 00:03:19,769
[Thanks to the clerk's directions]

94
00:03:19,769 --> 00:03:21,428
I see the Hanwoo* sign right there!

95
00:03:21,428 --> 00:03:23,129
- Oh, there it is.
- You see it?

96
00:03:23,129 --> 00:03:24,922
This way.

97
00:03:24,922 --> 00:03:26,483
Whoa, this place is packed.

98
00:03:26,483 --> 00:03:27,800
Geez, look at this crowd.

99
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,726
[Will it live up to Woo Shik's massive hype...]

100
00:03:29,726 --> 00:03:31,542
[7:03 PM at Hanwoo*]
Welcome in.

101
00:03:31,542 --> 00:03:33,605
- Hello.
- Good evening.

102
00:03:34,842 --> 00:03:37,343
How'd you guys track this place down?

103
00:03:37,343 --> 00:03:39,263
Then thanks to you, we'll dig in a little too.

104
00:03:39,263 --> 00:03:41,063
- Sounds good.
- Yes, it's a team dinner again today.

105
00:03:41,063 --> 00:03:43,593
- What should we get? The combo?
- About what we mentioned earlier...

106
00:03:43,593 --> 00:03:45,193
Let's get one small order of raw beef.

107
00:03:45,193 --> 00:03:47,959
- He went on and on about wanting mungtigi.
- Oh, that raw beef is the same thing?

108
00:03:47,959 --> 00:03:49,059
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

109
00:03:49,059 --> 00:03:51,142
[Same fresh meat, different cut]
- We can just get 300g of that too. - Right.

110
00:03:51,142 --> 00:03:53,303
Combo, 600 grams?

111
00:03:53,303 --> 00:03:54,523
What should we get?

112
00:03:54,523 --> 00:03:56,460
The combo.

113
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:58,842
[Taking your order]
- Hello. - Hello.

114
00:03:58,842 --> 00:04:00,266
My goodness, your face is so tiny.

115
00:04:00,266 --> 00:04:02,635
Your face is small too.

116
00:04:02,635 --> 00:04:03,412
[Kind words first, then the order]

117
00:04:03,412 --> 00:04:04,493
- You're lovely.
- Yeah.

118
00:04:04,493 --> 00:04:05,572
Thank you.

119
00:04:05,572 --> 00:04:08,827
- We'll have one order of raw beef, 300g.
- Got it.

120
00:04:08,827 --> 00:04:10,273
And the combo, 600g.

121
00:04:10,273 --> 00:04:13,393
- Combo 600, raw beef 300.
- Yeah.

122
00:04:13,393 --> 00:04:14,647
[The raw beef comes right out]
It's out already.

123
00:04:14,647 --> 00:04:15,848
Thank you.

124
00:04:15,848 --> 00:04:18,593
- Woo Shik, snap a few photos.
- Sure.

125
00:04:18,593 --> 00:04:21,754
[The pre-meal ritual, Director Choi's insert]
- Are you shooting an insert? - Yeah.

126
00:04:21,754 --> 00:04:24,056
[Behold Gwangju's famous raw beef]

127
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:26,625
[Warning, seriously chewy]

128
00:04:31,297 --> 00:04:32,932
[The director's intent, a mystery...]

129
00:04:32,932 --> 00:04:34,374
Let's dig in.

130
00:04:34,374 --> 00:04:36,536
The thing Woo Shik wanted so badly.

131
00:04:36,536 --> 00:04:38,852
I really wanted this so much.

132
00:04:39,872 --> 00:04:42,842
[Picking up one precious piece]

133
00:04:42,842 --> 00:04:45,444
[Taking a reverent bite]

134
00:04:47,346 --> 00:04:48,581
Is it really that good?

135
00:04:48,581 --> 00:04:49,815
[A slap to the forehead]

136
00:04:49,815 --> 00:04:50,426
[My turn then]

137
00:04:50,426 --> 00:04:52,026
Is it good?

138
00:04:52,026 --> 00:04:52,685
Huh?

139
00:04:52,685 --> 00:04:54,094
[Applause]
You dipped it in this sauce?

140
00:04:54,094 --> 00:04:55,726
This is ridiculously good.

141
00:04:55,726 --> 00:04:57,226
This is straight-up...

142
00:04:57,226 --> 00:04:59,158
Chewed it twice and it just melted away.

143
00:04:59,158 --> 00:05:00,826
[Are you sure?]

144
00:05:07,516 --> 00:05:09,068
[Chewed 21 times]

145
00:05:09,068 --> 00:05:11,519
[A taste worth hyping tenfold]

146
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,759
- Oh, this is so good.
- It's really good.

147
00:05:13,759 --> 00:05:14,992
Hey, excuse me.

148
00:05:14,992 --> 00:05:16,860
Do we eat this the exact same way?

149
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:19,035
[Brisket, Sesame oil]
Dip brisket in oil.

150
00:05:19,035 --> 00:05:20,059
Got it.

151
00:05:20,059 --> 00:05:23,708
Use sesame oil to bring out that savory taste.

152
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:27,553
I've never had raw brisket before in my life.

153
00:05:27,553 --> 00:05:29,380
But this right here is the game-changer.

154
00:05:29,380 --> 00:05:30,523
- The real game-changer.
- Yeah.

155
00:05:30,523 --> 00:05:31,724
[The kicker Seo Jun mentioned]

156
00:05:31,724 --> 00:05:33,659
[The red seasoning sauce]

157
00:05:33,659 --> 00:05:34,880
The red one?

158
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,028
This is the kicker.

159
00:05:36,028 --> 00:05:37,119
[A generous dip, a big bite]

160
00:05:37,119 --> 00:05:39,165
So good, this is really so good.

161
00:05:39,165 --> 00:05:40,227
[Glancing around]

162
00:05:40,227 --> 00:05:42,560
[The crew]
You all probably want to eat soon.

163
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:45,164
The owner said today's assorted platter

164
00:05:45,164 --> 00:05:48,407
- isn't looking too great today.
- I see.

165
00:05:48,407 --> 00:05:51,510
[The owner recommends other cuts]
So how about ribeye, hanger, or galbi instead,

166
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:52,878
is what she's recommending.

167
00:05:52,878 --> 00:05:55,975
How is everything here this good?

168
00:05:55,975 --> 00:05:56,955
Man, this is just too good.

169
00:05:56,955 --> 00:05:58,735
- In that case, we'll...
- Go with the hanger.

170
00:05:58,735 --> 00:05:59,593
- Go with the hanger.
- Hanger?

171
00:05:59,593 --> 00:06:01,520
- Yeah.
- Isn't that pricey, though?

172
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:03,359
We don't have a whole lot of money, so...

173
00:06:03,359 --> 00:06:04,757
in that case,

174
00:06:04,757 --> 00:06:06,892
- galbisal, 300 grams,
- Got it.

175
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:08,627
- And ribeye...
- ribeye, 300.

176
00:06:08,627 --> 00:06:09,760
- Sure.
- Sure.

177
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:12,480
- And one bottle of Ipsaeju, please.
- Sure.

178
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,366
- Is Ipsaeju a Gwangju soju?
- Yeah.

179
00:06:14,366 --> 00:06:15,501
[Receipt: raw beef &amp; galbisal, 87,000]

180
00:06:15,501 --> 00:06:18,127
[Again, food arrives the moment they order...]

181
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:19,071
What's this now?

182
00:06:19,071 --> 00:06:20,141
- Oh my.
- Seonji soup.

183
00:06:20,141 --> 00:06:22,408
Seonji soup?

184
00:06:22,408 --> 00:06:24,731
[The complimentary soup, seonji soup]

185
00:06:25,811 --> 00:06:28,970
[The rich broth aroma pours off the screen...]

186
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:31,516
[Takes a spoonful right away]
Huh, this seonji is the clear kind, though?

187
00:06:33,118 --> 00:06:34,553
[Slurp]

188
00:06:36,055 --> 00:06:38,441
[Seo Jun jumps right in too]

189
00:06:40,526 --> 00:06:42,359
Oh, that's good.

190
00:06:42,359 --> 00:06:43,521
- Oh, so good.
- Oh my.

191
00:06:43,521 --> 00:06:44,940
Come on.

192
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:46,261
This calls for a drink, quick!

193
00:06:46,261 --> 00:06:47,566
Load up!

194
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,261
[A taste that practically forces a toast...]

195
00:06:51,904 --> 00:06:54,173
[An honest "ahhh" of pure truth]

196
00:06:54,173 --> 00:06:55,092
[Back to the raw beef, one piece at a time...]

197
00:06:55,092 --> 00:06:57,101
- This is incredible.
- It's really good.

198
00:06:57,101 --> 00:06:59,000
Hold on.

199
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,079
Just hold on.

200
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:02,040
[The older ones all freeze up at once]

201
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,883
Go on, eat.

202
00:07:03,883 --> 00:07:06,793
[Unfazed by the camera swooping in]

203
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:08,413
Whoa.

204
00:07:09,092 --> 00:07:10,723
Whoa.

205
00:07:10,723 --> 00:07:13,024
[I'll show you how it's done myself]
Wait for it.

206
00:07:14,159 --> 00:07:15,261
Bring it up nice and slow.

207
00:07:15,261 --> 00:07:16,995
There we go.

208
00:07:20,299 --> 00:07:22,234
Whoa.

209
00:07:23,372 --> 00:07:25,570
You're being so fake right now.

210
00:07:26,305 --> 00:07:28,636
It's so good.

211
00:07:28,636 --> 00:07:30,542
Today, I'm honestly
the happiest I've ever been.

212
00:07:30,542 --> 00:07:33,437
If we'd gone to catch that boat,
we'd never have gotten to eat this.

213
00:07:33,437 --> 00:07:35,092
- Exactly.
- Right.

214
00:07:35,092 --> 00:07:37,437
If you hadn't dug into this,
couldn't you have made it to Jeju?

215
00:07:37,437 --> 00:07:40,002
Jeju? Where's that?

216
00:07:40,002 --> 00:07:41,463
I've forgotten every bit of it.

217
00:07:41,463 --> 00:07:43,722
Every memory I've had up to now
has just been wiped clean.

218
00:07:43,722 --> 00:07:45,424
[Raw beef has nothing to do with memory]
All because of this.

219
00:07:45,424 --> 00:07:46,726
Galbisal and ribeye here.

220
00:07:46,726 --> 00:07:48,527
- Hello.
- Hello.

221
00:07:48,527 --> 00:07:49,483
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you.

222
00:07:49,483 --> 00:07:50,496
[Right on cue, the main meat arrives]
Hello.

223
00:07:50,496 --> 00:07:51,523
How've you been?

224
00:07:51,523 --> 00:07:53,323
Yeah, you're so good-looking

225
00:07:53,323 --> 00:07:54,423
in person.

226
00:07:54,423 --> 00:07:56,802
[Ribeye 300g]
And you're absolutely beautiful too.

227
00:07:56,802 --> 00:07:58,296
- This is...
- Hold up. This is the galbisal.

228
00:07:58,296 --> 00:07:59,983
- Galbisal.
- Yes, over here.

229
00:07:59,983 --> 00:08:01,660
Once it heats up a little.

230
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:04,460
Your accent is getting weird.

231
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,603
How do people talk around here, dialect-wise?

232
00:08:05,603 --> 00:08:07,326
- Jeolla-do.
- Haetdangge.

233
00:08:07,326 --> 00:08:09,618
[How about picking up some Jeolla-do dialect?]
Haetdangge, geurangge.

234
00:08:09,618 --> 00:08:11,784
Ah, heobeonage mashitdai!

235
00:08:11,784 --> 00:08:13,185
[A terribly fake dialect]
So good.

236
00:08:13,185 --> 00:08:16,198
How do you say "delicious" in this dialect?

237
00:08:16,198 --> 00:08:17,858
Something like "jjeonda."

238
00:08:17,858 --> 00:08:19,198
Mashitdaing.

239
00:08:19,198 --> 00:08:20,659
Daebaksakeon?

240
00:08:20,659 --> 00:08:21,562
Sorry?

241
00:08:21,562 --> 00:08:23,179
- Daebak...
- Daebaksakeon.

242
00:08:23,179 --> 00:08:25,959
- Mashitdaing.
- Atta daebaksakeon.

243
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:28,533
Atta daebaksakeon mashitneing.

244
00:08:29,626 --> 00:08:31,698
[Such eager learners]
Daebaksakeon mashitgumeon.

245
00:08:31,698 --> 00:08:32,639
Mashitdangge.

246
00:08:32,639 --> 00:08:34,078
Mashitdangge.

247
00:08:34,078 --> 00:08:36,008
- Looks like it's ready.
- Go ahead, eat.

248
00:08:36,008 --> 00:08:37,109
[Grill master Woo Shik]

249
00:08:37,109 --> 00:08:40,061
- That's a one-bite piece.
- Just one bite.

250
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,042
Cook it up.

251
00:08:41,042 --> 00:08:43,282
[Bite-sized slices of galbisal]
Atta guweobeollangge.

252
00:08:43,282 --> 00:08:44,683
Should I grill them little by little?

253
00:08:44,683 --> 00:08:47,019
- Just eat them as they come.
- Let us taste it first.

254
00:08:47,019 --> 00:08:48,527
[Lining them up neatly on the grill]

255
00:08:49,922 --> 00:08:51,781
I feel like I'll get hungry
on the way back to the place.

256
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:52,942
Then grab a whole chicken to go.

257
00:08:52,942 --> 00:08:54,626
Yeah, a whole chicken.

258
00:08:54,626 --> 00:08:57,421
What time does Yeongdong Market close?

259
00:08:57,421 --> 00:08:58,762
Nine o'clock.

260
00:08:58,762 --> 00:09:00,193
They even deliver.

261
00:09:00,193 --> 00:09:01,681
All the way here?

262
00:09:01,681 --> 00:09:02,862
The market does delivery?

263
00:09:02,862 --> 00:09:05,930
But apparently that chicken place
has a few branches.

264
00:09:05,930 --> 00:09:08,927
The thing is, we don't have our phones.

265
00:09:08,927 --> 00:09:10,110
Oh, right.

266
00:09:10,110 --> 00:09:12,251
So when we get our phones back later,
should we order chicken?

267
00:09:12,251 --> 00:09:14,671
You can't order in 1 minute 30 seconds.

268
00:09:14,671 --> 00:09:17,059
Chicken challenge?

269
00:09:17,059 --> 00:09:19,650
- Let's try it.
- Later, we'll give it a shot.

270
00:09:19,650 --> 00:09:23,122
[A moment later]
All right, here we go, start.

271
00:09:23,122 --> 00:09:25,226
[Clinking]

272
00:09:25,226 --> 00:09:26,891
- Hey.
- Hey.

273
00:09:28,727 --> 00:09:32,264
[That's right, during the phone chance]

274
00:09:32,264 --> 00:09:35,292
[Shortly after, the new rules are revealed]
- Just put it in for now. - Got it.

275
00:09:35,292 --> 00:09:37,552
- Going for it.
- Here I go.

276
00:09:37,552 --> 00:09:40,592
[The galbisal sizzles to a perfect finish]
This needs to be eaten right about now.

277
00:09:40,592 --> 00:09:41,674
- Diving in.
- Eating.

278
00:09:41,674 --> 00:09:43,062
Same here.

279
00:09:48,648 --> 00:09:50,516
So good.

280
00:09:50,516 --> 00:09:54,221
[Woo Shik dunks his in the oil dip]

281
00:09:54,221 --> 00:09:56,321
Tastes amazing.

282
00:09:56,321 --> 00:09:57,356
[Hand clamped over mouth]

283
00:09:57,356 --> 00:09:58,792
[Flailing in delight]

284
00:09:58,792 --> 00:10:01,393
Atta daebaksakeon.

285
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:07,426
- This is the one.
- Seriously chewy.

286
00:10:07,426 --> 00:10:09,568
- Yeah, real chewy.
- So chewy.

287
00:10:09,568 --> 00:10:10,903
Yeah, this is it.

288
00:10:10,903 --> 00:10:12,871
It's delicious.

289
00:10:12,871 --> 00:10:15,775
[Vanishing into mouths nonstop...]

290
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:18,944
Next round, we wrap it in lettuce.

291
00:10:18,944 --> 00:10:20,183
[Big chomp]

292
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:23,526
[Clapping seal appears]
Save that for last.

293
00:10:23,526 --> 00:10:26,847
This only shows up when Seo Jun's
in a really good mood.

294
00:10:26,847 --> 00:10:28,407
I won't even do this for my own mom.

295
00:10:28,407 --> 00:10:30,293
What did he just do?

296
00:10:30,293 --> 00:10:32,547
[Encore]
You really don't catch this often.

297
00:10:32,547 --> 00:10:35,131
I was right beside him, totally missed it.

298
00:10:35,131 --> 00:10:36,931
Looks like this won't be enough, huh?

299
00:10:36,931 --> 00:10:39,932
- This is all the meat we've got left?
- Yeah.

300
00:10:39,932 --> 00:10:41,271
What's the plan for Jeju?

301
00:10:41,271 --> 00:10:42,568
Not going.

302
00:10:42,568 --> 00:10:44,470
[Jeju shrinks to nothing before Hanwoo...]

303
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:47,773
Let's just hit Jeju on our own next time.

304
00:10:47,773 --> 00:10:50,252
For today, let's blow
every last won right here.

305
00:10:50,252 --> 00:10:51,331
Sounds good.

306
00:10:51,331 --> 00:10:53,880
Any chance we could borrow on tomorrow's, too?

307
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,815
This really is something else.

308
00:10:56,815 --> 00:10:59,952
[Mr. Banker, send all the loans this way]

309
00:10:59,952 --> 00:11:01,853
What a find, real find.

310
00:11:02,756 --> 00:11:05,457
And right now I'm really hyped
for the tteokguk.

311
00:11:05,457 --> 00:11:07,026
[Time for dessert]

312
00:11:07,026 --> 00:11:08,551
What can I get you?

313
00:11:08,551 --> 00:11:09,828
Two dessert tteokguks.

314
00:11:09,828 --> 00:11:11,230
- Two dessert tteokguks?
- Yes.

315
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,131
[Total 150,000]

316
00:11:12,131 --> 00:11:14,477
Isn't it wild
that a barbecue place sells tteokguk?

317
00:11:14,477 --> 00:11:15,734
Still, no clue why they sell it.

318
00:11:15,734 --> 00:11:17,893
According to him, lots of spots sell it.

319
00:11:17,893 --> 00:11:19,897
In Gwangju,
barbecue spots serve it for dessert.

320
00:11:19,897 --> 00:11:20,739
For real?

321
00:11:20,739 --> 00:11:22,316
Tteokguk's here.

322
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:24,756
[Enters with a warm hello]
- Hello. - Hello.

323
00:11:24,756 --> 00:11:26,557
- The black pepper smells nice.
- Yeah, the pepper's great.

324
00:11:26,557 --> 00:11:28,316
[Namdo specialty: barbecue-house tteokguk]
All right, here we go.

325
00:11:28,316 --> 00:11:30,476
This is my first time having tteokguk
at a barbecue place.

326
00:11:30,476 --> 00:11:32,317
- Same here.
- Start with the broth.

327
00:11:32,317 --> 00:11:34,152
[Nice to meet you, first bite incoming]

328
00:11:35,387 --> 00:11:37,455
The rice cakes are unreal.

329
00:11:39,858 --> 00:11:41,120
[Hand to mouth, speechless]

330
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,927
Kind of has that Lunar New Year at home feel.

331
00:11:43,927 --> 00:11:45,357
- Super clean taste.
- Tastes like homemade?

332
00:11:45,357 --> 00:11:47,057
- It's seriously good.
- So clean and so tasty.

333
00:11:47,057 --> 00:11:48,477
Tastes just like homemade.

334
00:11:48,477 --> 00:11:51,136
But eating this at a barbecue spot
is so different.

335
00:11:51,136 --> 00:11:52,617
Right, I've seen dessert naengmyeon before,

336
00:11:52,617 --> 00:11:54,640
- but dessert tteokguk is a first.
- Yeah.

337
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:56,708
[Warning: you might age a year...]

338
00:11:56,708 --> 00:11:58,893
Hey, this is the move.

339
00:11:58,893 --> 00:12:00,712
This is the one.

340
00:12:01,313 --> 00:12:04,181
[Tops the rice cake with kimchi, huge bite]

341
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:08,321
Eating it with kimchi is just perfect.

342
00:12:08,321 --> 00:12:10,861
So how's it stack up? Where does this rank?

343
00:12:10,861 --> 00:12:12,242
- Number one.
- Number one?

344
00:12:12,242 --> 00:12:13,092
- Wait, number one?
- Yeah.

345
00:12:13,092 --> 00:12:14,226
Are you serious?

346
00:12:14,226 --> 00:12:16,982
- Worth a trip all the way to Gwangju.
- Definitely.

347
00:12:16,982 --> 00:12:18,263
That was so good.

348
00:12:18,263 --> 00:12:20,999
It'd been forever since I had raw beef,

349
00:12:20,999 --> 00:12:23,602
and it hit the spot,
the tteokguk hit even harder,

350
00:12:23,602 --> 00:12:26,781
everything was just delicious.

351
00:12:26,781 --> 00:12:29,875
- Tomorrow's our last night, isn't it?
- Yeah.

352
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:32,593
So nailing down where we go really matters.

353
00:12:32,593 --> 00:12:33,982
Here's the thing though,

354
00:12:33,982 --> 00:12:37,283
- the reason I still can't let Jeju go is...
- I haven't given up on it either.

355
00:12:37,283 --> 00:12:38,760
[Woo Shik's Plan]
We land in Jeju tomorrow,

356
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:41,343
we squeeze the most out of Jeju,

357
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:44,763
then catching a flight to Gimpo
would be easiest for us.

358
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:48,603
The return ticket is already over 100 grand.
You knew that, right?

359
00:12:48,603 --> 00:12:50,259
Hey, but once we land in Jeju,

360
00:12:50,259 --> 00:12:52,463
we earn money there and come back out.

361
00:12:53,098 --> 00:12:54,422
The heck are you talking about?

362
00:12:54,422 --> 00:12:56,969
We'll pick up part-time jobs there.

363
00:12:56,969 --> 00:12:57,836
[Wasted my focus on that one...]

364
00:12:57,836 --> 00:12:59,261
Man, what nonsense.

365
00:12:59,261 --> 00:13:01,922
No really, I want to squeeze it out
and make this work, honestly.

366
00:13:01,922 --> 00:13:04,522
- Yeah.
- Then how about this?

367
00:13:04,522 --> 00:13:06,042
There's that early morning ferry,

368
00:13:06,042 --> 00:13:07,362
the one at 1 AM.

369
00:13:07,362 --> 00:13:09,862
Today's the only shot.
If we're going, it has to be 1 AM tonight.

370
00:13:09,862 --> 00:13:10,782
Let's just go now.

371
00:13:10,782 --> 00:13:12,618
If we're going, it has to be 1 AM tonight.

372
00:13:12,618 --> 00:13:14,286
[Q. So, you haven't given up on Jeju?]

373
00:13:14,286 --> 00:13:15,622
We're making this happen.

374
00:13:15,622 --> 00:13:17,021
Let's just go for it.

375
00:13:17,021 --> 00:13:19,762
Not just me. Everyone's locked in on this.

376
00:13:19,762 --> 00:13:22,127
If we're all on the same page,

377
00:13:22,127 --> 00:13:24,529
I'm ready to give it everything we've got.

378
00:13:24,529 --> 00:13:25,842
I'll get to Jeju.

379
00:13:25,842 --> 00:13:28,059
I'll make it to Jeju, no question.

380
00:13:28,059 --> 00:13:30,952
[A. Not a soul had given up]

381
00:13:30,952 --> 00:13:32,992
- Thanks so much.
- Thank you.

382
00:13:32,992 --> 00:13:35,373
[Dinner: -150,000 won, Balance: 72,810 won]
Thanks for the great meal.

383
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,278
I'm stuffed.

384
00:13:39,278 --> 00:13:40,912
Do you want some fruit?

385
00:13:40,912 --> 00:13:42,053
How about strawberries?

386
00:13:42,053 --> 00:13:43,293
- But...
- We've got plenty of money left, though.

387
00:13:43,293 --> 00:13:44,333
Yeah, there's a lot left.

388
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,118
- If something's open on the way.
- Right.

389
00:13:46,118 --> 00:13:47,273
- You know that corner near our place.
- Yeah.

390
00:13:47,273 --> 00:13:49,388
- Right.
- Right by our place.

391
00:13:49,388 --> 00:13:51,526
I just called it "our place."

392
00:13:51,526 --> 00:13:52,858
It's officially home now.

393
00:13:52,858 --> 00:13:54,593
[Heading back to their already-beloved home]

394
00:13:54,593 --> 00:13:58,607
[A 25-minute walk from the restaurant home]

395
00:13:59,251 --> 00:14:01,952
Just keep walking ahead for a bit.

396
00:14:01,952 --> 00:14:03,992
- I have a massive emergency right now.
- For real?

397
00:14:03,992 --> 00:14:06,139
There was a restroom right back there.

398
00:14:06,139 --> 00:14:09,975
We're filming,
so I'll slip away alone in a bit.

399
00:14:09,975 --> 00:14:12,411
[Trying to hold it in for a moment...]

400
00:14:12,411 --> 00:14:14,046
[Tsk...]

401
00:14:14,046 --> 00:14:16,181
[Sigh]

402
00:14:16,181 --> 00:14:19,751
[Eyes darting around]

403
00:14:19,751 --> 00:14:21,921
[Face turning pale]

404
00:14:21,921 --> 00:14:23,760
My bladder's about to burst at this rate.

405
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,845
Get in there fast!

406
00:14:24,845 --> 00:14:26,058
This is bad.

407
00:14:26,058 --> 00:14:27,359
Pop in over there.

408
00:14:27,359 --> 00:14:29,126
- This is a disaster.
- Is this a Code Red?

409
00:14:29,126 --> 00:14:31,626
Full-blown emergency.

410
00:14:31,626 --> 00:14:33,193
[Still about 15 minutes from home]
Move it.

411
00:14:33,193 --> 00:14:36,660
[Bladder Code Red]
This is a real emergency now.

412
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:39,472
- My palms are sweating right now.
- Let me see.

413
00:14:39,472 --> 00:14:41,099
Hold on, just pop into that cafe.

414
00:14:41,099 --> 00:14:43,385
[Spots a coffee shop one block ahead]
- Go on. - Be right back.

415
00:14:43,385 --> 00:14:44,686
Throw on your cap before you go in.

416
00:14:44,686 --> 00:14:47,412
[Seo Jun worried about Woo Shik's image]
- This is a crisis. - Choi Woo Shik...

417
00:14:49,053 --> 00:14:50,682
Restroom on the second floor?

418
00:14:50,682 --> 00:14:52,951
[Big grin]

419
00:14:52,951 --> 00:14:54,665
Be right back.

420
00:14:55,393 --> 00:14:56,988
[Woo Shik takes off for the restroom]
Cap on.

421
00:14:56,988 --> 00:14:59,518
[Cap pulled down tight, just like Seo Jun said]

422
00:15:01,393 --> 00:15:04,830
[Feet, don't fail me now]

423
00:15:06,259 --> 00:15:07,726
Hold on.

424
00:15:07,726 --> 00:15:08,821
Ouch, my stomach.

425
00:15:08,821 --> 00:15:10,369
- My stomach hurts.
- I can't stop laughing.

426
00:15:10,369 --> 00:15:12,437
Way too funny.

427
00:15:12,437 --> 00:15:15,753
[Thanks, Tu*...]

428
00:15:15,753 --> 00:15:17,585
Looks like he's coming back down.

429
00:15:17,585 --> 00:15:20,178
Catch his face on camera really well.

430
00:15:21,393 --> 00:15:25,814
[The long-awaited Woo Shik walks out]

431
00:15:25,814 --> 00:15:28,754
- How was it?
- You said you wanted one,

432
00:15:28,754 --> 00:15:30,345
so I grabbed this.

433
00:15:30,345 --> 00:15:31,566
- Oh really?
- Yeah.

434
00:15:31,566 --> 00:15:32,546
Thanks.

435
00:15:32,546 --> 00:15:34,559
[Balance: 71,410 won]
- What's that? - Sweet potato bar.

436
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:35,872
[Moving on]

437
00:15:35,872 --> 00:15:36,866
How was it?

438
00:15:36,866 --> 00:15:38,026
- Huh?
- How was it?

439
00:15:38,026 --> 00:15:40,298
It was great, the sweet potato bar.

440
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,734
- Okay.
- Yeah.

441
00:15:43,535 --> 00:15:45,825
Yeah, nice and clean as expected.

442
00:15:45,825 --> 00:15:46,863
Let's get moving.

443
00:15:46,863 --> 00:15:48,144
Let's pick up some snacks.

444
00:15:48,144 --> 00:15:49,084
Sure, ice cream?

445
00:15:49,084 --> 00:15:51,309
Hold on though, you know
how much cash we have left?

446
00:15:51,309 --> 00:15:53,083
Over 70,000 won.

447
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,780
[Current balance: 71,410 won]
Right, plenty left.

448
00:15:56,381 --> 00:15:59,081
[Strolling along with their fat wallet]

449
00:15:59,081 --> 00:16:00,124
For dessert.

450
00:16:00,124 --> 00:16:01,469
[Arriving at the mart by their place]
Hello.

451
00:16:01,469 --> 00:16:03,003
Hello.

452
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:04,904
Huh? I want something refreshing.

453
00:16:04,904 --> 00:16:06,244
Ten for 5,000 won.

454
00:16:06,244 --> 00:16:07,492
Ten for 5,000 won?

455
00:16:07,492 --> 00:16:10,044
- Should we treat everyone?
- We'll grab ten and share them around.

456
00:16:10,044 --> 00:16:11,404
You're treating us with that cash?

457
00:16:11,404 --> 00:16:13,143
- Yes.
- Of course.

458
00:16:13,143 --> 00:16:14,464
We're loaded right now.

459
00:16:14,464 --> 00:16:15,834
I want the pina colada.

460
00:16:15,834 --> 00:16:17,804
In the basket.

461
00:16:17,804 --> 00:16:19,906
I'll go with the Crun* King.

462
00:16:19,906 --> 00:16:21,509
Mo*to bar for me.

463
00:16:21,509 --> 00:16:22,941
That's it. Done.

464
00:16:22,941 --> 00:16:24,744
[Picking out plenty, then heading to pay]

465
00:16:24,744 --> 00:16:27,011
Hang on, are only the bars on sale?

466
00:16:27,946 --> 00:16:30,309
[Seo Jun's Crun* King isn't a bar type]
Bars only.

467
00:16:30,309 --> 00:16:31,450
- Bars only, huh.
- It's fine.

468
00:16:31,450 --> 00:16:32,890
- It's just one.
- Right.

469
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:34,119
- We can just buy it.
- Sure.

470
00:16:34,119 --> 00:16:35,493
[Her green light closes the case]

471
00:16:35,493 --> 00:16:37,622
That's 6,400 won.

472
00:16:38,726 --> 00:16:40,393
[Balance: 65,010 won]
- Yeah. - Thank you.

473
00:16:40,393 --> 00:16:41,626
- Thank you.
- Yes.

474
00:16:41,626 --> 00:16:43,094
- Take care.
- Yes.

475
00:16:43,094 --> 00:16:45,056
[The rich folks who dropped 6,400 won]

476
00:16:45,056 --> 00:16:46,382
All right.

477
00:16:46,382 --> 00:16:48,834
We've got way too much money left.

478
00:16:48,834 --> 00:16:50,929
[Shopping wrapped]

479
00:16:51,603 --> 00:16:53,092
Can I dig in?

480
00:16:53,092 --> 00:16:55,140
Cookies and cream for me.

481
00:16:55,140 --> 00:16:57,560
[Ice cream distribution kicks off]

482
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,393
[Woo Shik gets the cookies and cream]

483
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,180
[Crew also gets ice cream]
- Thank you. - Thank you.

484
00:17:01,180 --> 00:17:03,616
You're broke and still treating us like this.

485
00:17:03,616 --> 00:17:05,878
We're rich right now.

486
00:17:06,618 --> 00:17:09,588
Even buying this,
we still have way too much left.

487
00:17:09,588 --> 00:17:10,822
[Munch]
[Nom]

488
00:17:10,822 --> 00:17:13,024
[Yum]

489
00:17:13,024 --> 00:17:18,510
[The trio roams Ssangchon eating ice cream]

490
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:19,491
Take a right.

491
00:17:19,491 --> 00:17:21,023
After the right turn.

492
00:17:21,023 --> 00:17:23,102
[The walk home, now easy]
Right turn, straight, then left.

493
00:17:23,102 --> 00:17:25,136
Straight.

494
00:17:25,136 --> 00:17:28,240
[They quickly reach their alley]

495
00:17:29,176 --> 00:17:31,209
What a sweet location.

496
00:17:32,847 --> 00:17:34,380
This is heavy.

497
00:17:34,380 --> 00:17:35,560
I lost my grip.

498
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,649
- Sorry.
- Head up.

499
00:17:37,649 --> 00:17:39,451
[Back at the lodging]

500
00:17:39,451 --> 00:17:40,552
Come on in.

501
00:17:40,552 --> 00:17:42,854
[9:10 PM, Gwangju lodging]

502
00:17:44,789 --> 00:17:47,760
[Spot anything suspicious on screen?]

503
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,496
Hey, our phones are right here.

504
00:17:49,496 --> 00:17:51,259
Huh? What's that?

505
00:17:51,259 --> 00:17:52,397
What is it?

506
00:17:52,397 --> 00:17:53,526
[As for what this is...]

507
00:17:53,526 --> 00:17:55,700
What's the plan?

508
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,470
[2026 S/S new arrival, Phone Jail]

509
00:17:58,470 --> 00:18:01,273
[Safely locked up tight]

510
00:18:01,273 --> 00:18:03,560
I really want to crack this open.

511
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,077
Hey Siri.

512
00:18:05,077 --> 00:18:06,293
[Summoning AI]
Hey Siri?

513
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:08,413
- The heck is this?
- Hey Siri.

514
00:18:08,413 --> 00:18:09,696
[Fiddling]

515
00:18:09,696 --> 00:18:10,860
Oh, right.

516
00:18:10,860 --> 00:18:12,137
[Screen auto-lights with movement]
Let me see who messaged me.

517
00:18:12,137 --> 00:18:13,718
Hold up.

518
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:14,953
[Rattle]

519
00:18:14,953 --> 00:18:18,023
[Rattle]
Huh? The phone next to it...

520
00:18:18,023 --> 00:18:19,526
- No, this one.
- Hey, it turned on.

521
00:18:19,526 --> 00:18:21,384
Let's do that.

522
00:18:21,384 --> 00:18:23,595
Phone chance.

523
00:18:23,595 --> 00:18:27,832
[Three sit down to use
Travel Restriction No. 3]

524
00:18:27,832 --> 00:18:28,858
[Staring...]

525
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:31,269
[Fiddling...]

526
00:18:31,269 --> 00:18:33,238
So what are we using the phone chance for?

527
00:18:33,238 --> 00:18:37,343
Truth is, I didn't eat enough earlier.

528
00:18:37,343 --> 00:18:39,024
I'm kind of in the mood for chicken and beer.

529
00:18:39,024 --> 00:18:40,328
- Chicken and beer?
- Yeah.

530
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:41,249
Su* Chicken?

531
00:18:41,249 --> 00:18:43,144
Let's grab one half-and-half from Su* Chicken.

532
00:18:43,144 --> 00:18:44,849
- Sounds perfect.
- Yeah.

533
00:18:44,849 --> 00:18:46,481
Where's our address again?

534
00:18:46,481 --> 00:18:49,782
Oh, I've got it, over there.
It's in that jacket.

535
00:18:49,782 --> 00:18:51,602
So we have to order it
in a minute thirty, right?

536
00:18:51,602 --> 00:18:52,962
But the rules are a little different this time.

537
00:18:52,962 --> 00:18:55,221
- I'll walk you through it once you sit.
- Okay.

538
00:18:55,221 --> 00:18:58,101
Last round, each person
got a minute thirty as a relay.

539
00:18:58,101 --> 00:19:01,633
[If it was a three-person relay before]
- Okay. - Thanks.

540
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,593
So what's changed about the rules?

541
00:19:03,593 --> 00:19:05,403
[The newly changed phone chance is...]
1 minute, 30 seconds.

542
00:19:05,403 --> 00:19:07,692
You'll have three minutes total.

543
00:19:07,692 --> 00:19:09,407
But the keys...

544
00:19:09,407 --> 00:19:10,544
[Pausing for effect]

545
00:19:10,544 --> 00:19:12,510
I'll be handing you quite a lot of them.

546
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:14,479
[Oh...]

547
00:19:14,479 --> 00:19:16,014
Open it within three minutes.

548
00:19:16,014 --> 00:19:17,983
[Unlock and use in three minutes]

549
00:19:17,983 --> 00:19:19,851
[Find the real key among these]

550
00:19:19,851 --> 00:19:22,721
[Then take out the phone and use it]

551
00:19:22,721 --> 00:19:25,340
[But after three minutes, it relocks]

552
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:26,610
The keys are in one big bunch?

553
00:19:26,610 --> 00:19:27,710
Let me show you first.

554
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:29,070
But shouldn't they be separated?

555
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:33,231
The three keys are each in here.

556
00:19:33,231 --> 00:19:35,533
[Oh...]

557
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:36,910
- How do we even unlock that?
- How do we open it?

558
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:38,669
How do the three of us
unlock it at the same time?

559
00:19:38,669 --> 00:19:40,605
Then hold on a sec.

560
00:19:40,605 --> 00:19:43,708
What if we pull a few out at a time...

561
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:47,545
and split them into chunks,
one for you, one for me, like that?

562
00:19:47,545 --> 00:19:49,749
- That does seem faster.
- Right?

563
00:19:49,749 --> 00:19:50,944
Will it come apart, though?

564
00:19:50,944 --> 00:19:52,126
Think it'll come apart? How's it look?

565
00:19:52,126 --> 00:19:53,652
I think it will.

566
00:19:53,652 --> 00:19:55,120
I've got a feeling right now.

567
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,155
Then untangle it
and hand them out to us at once.

568
00:19:57,155 --> 00:19:57,889
[Woo MacGyver]
Okay.

569
00:19:57,889 --> 00:19:59,059
All right then, we're starting.

570
00:19:59,059 --> 00:20:01,192
Oh, hold on a sec.

571
00:20:01,192 --> 00:20:03,927
[Sizing it up]

572
00:20:03,927 --> 00:20:05,392
Just feel it out.

573
00:20:05,392 --> 00:20:06,431
I don't think so.

574
00:20:06,431 --> 00:20:07,393
- No?
- Right?

575
00:20:07,393 --> 00:20:08,305
I don't think it'll come apart.

576
00:20:08,305 --> 00:20:10,735
- It's not looking like it'll come apart, huh?
- Yeah.

577
00:20:10,735 --> 00:20:14,146
[Quietly checking it once more...]

578
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:15,173
- We starting?
- Yeah.

579
00:20:15,173 --> 00:20:17,642
All right, here we go. Start!

580
00:20:17,642 --> 00:20:19,193
[Chance is on]

581
00:20:19,193 --> 00:20:22,981
[Woo MacGyver starts untangling right away]

582
00:20:22,981 --> 00:20:25,133
[Spinning]

583
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:26,159
Hey, just stick it in.

584
00:20:26,159 --> 00:20:27,627
No, it's coming loose.

585
00:20:27,627 --> 00:20:29,092
No, it's coming loose.

586
00:20:29,092 --> 00:20:30,493
[Got it open!]
Hey!

587
00:20:30,493 --> 00:20:32,724
[Splitting up the keys]
Hand it here.

588
00:20:32,724 --> 00:20:35,794
[Total mess]

589
00:20:35,794 --> 00:20:38,630
[Yumi's first try, fail]
- Just try it. - Got it.

590
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:41,026
[Fail 2, Fail 3]

591
00:20:41,026 --> 00:20:42,568
Huh?

592
00:20:42,568 --> 00:20:44,538
Not it.

593
00:20:44,538 --> 00:20:47,038
- This isn't it.
- It's not.

594
00:20:47,707 --> 00:20:49,193
- Just try it.
- Got it.

595
00:20:49,193 --> 00:20:50,626
[As they struggle to find the right key...]
Hold on.

596
00:20:50,626 --> 00:20:52,343
- Not it.
- That's one minute down.

597
00:20:52,343 --> 00:20:53,793
Try it like this.

598
00:20:53,793 --> 00:20:55,593
All right, guys!

599
00:20:55,593 --> 00:20:57,115
Guys, it's the black one.

600
00:20:57,115 --> 00:20:59,751
- Yeah, I think it's black.
- It's black.

601
00:20:59,751 --> 00:21:03,288
[Figured out it's black, not silver]

602
00:21:03,288 --> 00:21:05,427
[They focus on the black keys, but...]

603
00:21:05,427 --> 00:21:06,526
This isn't the one.

604
00:21:06,526 --> 00:21:08,793
Hey, it's open!

605
00:21:08,793 --> 00:21:11,125
Hey, it's open!

606
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:12,460
[Woo Shik's phone freed]

607
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:14,267
Quick.

608
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:16,893
- Su* Chicken?
- Yeah.

609
00:21:16,893 --> 00:21:19,070
Su* Chicken.

610
00:21:19,771 --> 00:21:21,530
[Loading...]

611
00:21:24,109 --> 00:21:26,851
[Nothing to show as 1:30 ticks by]

612
00:21:27,612 --> 00:21:31,326
[The wrong-key pile keeps growing...]

613
00:21:31,326 --> 00:21:33,493
Oh, hey, it's open!

614
00:21:33,493 --> 00:21:36,126
[Seo Jun's phone freed]
Oh, hey, it's open!

615
00:21:36,126 --> 00:21:38,923
<i>Hi, this is Su* Chicken.</i>

616
00:21:38,923 --> 00:21:40,660
[Unlocking, Searching, On the call]

617
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:42,595
<i>With carefully selected ingredients
and seasoning...</i>

618
00:21:42,595 --> 00:21:44,025
<i>- Yes, this is Su* Chicken.</i>
- Yeah, hello.

619
00:21:44,025 --> 00:21:47,864
Are you delivering right now?

620
00:21:47,864 --> 00:21:49,534
<i>- For pickup?</i>
- Yeah... no.

621
00:21:49,534 --> 00:21:51,326
- Delivery.
<i>- Delivery?</i>

622
00:21:51,326 --> 00:21:53,726
<i>- What's the address?</i>
- Ssangchon-dong.

623
00:21:53,726 --> 00:21:56,827
<i>For Ssangchon-dong,
the delivery fee runs pretty high.</i>

624
00:21:56,827 --> 00:22:00,385
So which branch would be closest
to Ssangchon-dong?

625
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:03,164
Hold on, I'm typing in Ssangchon-dong.

626
00:22:03,164 --> 00:22:05,404
One minute left now.

627
00:22:05,404 --> 00:22:07,585
<i>- Want me to tell you the nearest branch?</i>
- Yes.

628
00:22:07,585 --> 00:22:09,053
Sure, one moment please.

629
00:22:09,053 --> 00:22:10,088
[Beep]

630
00:22:10,088 --> 00:22:12,173
Wait...

631
00:22:12,173 --> 00:22:14,325
[The call dropped!]
Wait...

632
00:22:14,325 --> 00:22:17,239
[The call got cut off by accident...]

633
00:22:17,239 --> 00:22:19,564
Su* Chicken.

634
00:22:19,564 --> 00:22:22,567
[Jumping in to help search]

635
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:26,597
[A lonely battle over here]

636
00:22:26,597 --> 00:22:28,907
Hey, I'm searching and nothing's showing up.

637
00:22:28,907 --> 00:22:32,010
[Searching Seo Jun is their only hope...]

638
00:22:32,010 --> 00:22:34,712
[30 seconds left]

639
00:22:36,414 --> 00:22:39,951
[Yumi's phone freed too]

640
00:22:39,951 --> 00:22:42,680
[Joining the search late]

641
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,821
Jinwol branch.

642
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:44,981
- Jinwol branch.
- Jinwol branch.

643
00:22:44,981 --> 00:22:47,720
[Just dial the number they found!]
This is it, this is the one.

644
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:50,159
[Pressed it!]
This is it.

645
00:22:50,159 --> 00:22:51,403
<i>Thanks for calling...</i>

646
00:22:51,403 --> 00:22:52,730
Time's up.

647
00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:53,860
<i>The finest taste and care...</i>

648
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:55,200
Time's up.

649
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:57,435
[Three minutes done]
<i>The finest taste and care...</i>

650
00:22:57,435 --> 00:23:00,206
<i>This is Su* Chicken.</i>

651
00:23:00,206 --> 00:23:01,573
I just found it.

652
00:23:01,573 --> 00:23:03,241
[Timed out right after finding the number...]
Is that the one?

653
00:23:03,241 --> 00:23:05,944
[Woo Shik whose call got rejected]

654
00:23:05,944 --> 00:23:08,046
[Just got a touch of the phone]

655
00:23:08,046 --> 00:23:10,215
[A maddening three-combo]

656
00:23:10,215 --> 00:23:12,250
[Back in lockup]

657
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:14,759
[The phones are taking their leave]

658
00:23:14,759 --> 00:23:17,648
- The strategy was solid, wasn't it?
- It was.

659
00:23:19,657 --> 00:23:21,899
- We did unlock the keys...
- Yeah.

660
00:23:21,899 --> 00:23:24,092
[Headache]
My head.

661
00:23:24,092 --> 00:23:25,519
That's a real bummer.

662
00:23:25,519 --> 00:23:28,092
This feels a little like
when we didn't make it to Jeju earlier.

663
00:23:28,092 --> 00:23:29,293
Yeah.

664
00:23:29,293 --> 00:23:32,380
Maybe we should've just ordered it
even with the high delivery fee.

665
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:34,331
- Right.
- Right.

666
00:23:34,331 --> 00:23:38,328
[For the trio missing late-night snacks...]

667
00:23:40,044 --> 00:23:43,177
[Just tonight, a special late-night treat]

668
00:23:43,177 --> 00:23:45,683
- What is it?
- Salmon steak.

669
00:23:45,683 --> 00:23:48,086
[Peel back the outer wrapping a bit]

670
00:23:48,086 --> 00:23:50,576
[Pop the whole container in the microwave]

671
00:23:50,576 --> 00:23:51,623
One minute.

672
00:23:51,623 --> 00:23:54,092
[Just one minute and it's done!]

673
00:23:54,092 --> 00:23:55,827
Whoa...

674
00:23:55,827 --> 00:23:58,162
The portion's pretty big.

675
00:23:58,162 --> 00:23:59,864
[A bite right away]

676
00:23:59,864 --> 00:24:00,693
[Eyes lighting up]

677
00:24:00,693 --> 00:24:02,466
- It's good.
- Yeah.

678
00:24:04,369 --> 00:24:05,657
- It's good.
- Yeah.

679
00:24:05,657 --> 00:24:08,706
- This is clean and tender, no fishy taste.
- Yeah.

680
00:24:08,706 --> 00:24:11,037
Really, no fishy smell at all.

681
00:24:11,037 --> 00:24:14,460
If you saute some pasta and toss this on top...

682
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:17,448
[Recipe ideas pouring out]
Over pasta would be amazing.

683
00:24:17,448 --> 00:24:19,797
- For one, it's easy.
- Yeah, true.

684
00:24:19,797 --> 00:24:21,817
[Right up his alley]
This is good.

685
00:24:21,817 --> 00:24:23,222
- Seriously good.
- Yeah.

686
00:24:23,222 --> 00:24:25,491
[After a satisfying late-night snack...]
We finished it all.

687
00:24:25,491 --> 00:24:28,293
[11:30 PM, Seo Jun &amp; Woo Shik's room]

688
00:24:28,293 --> 00:24:30,738
[Snack's done, time for bed!]

689
00:24:30,738 --> 00:24:33,131
The blanket here is cute.

690
00:24:33,131 --> 00:24:34,959
[Just when sleep was coming, though...]

691
00:24:34,959 --> 00:24:36,359
Hey, there's no window in here?

692
00:24:36,359 --> 00:24:37,470
We're going in March...

693
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:39,560
[A man back at the laptop]
Oh, but that's tomorrow.

694
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:40,827
Tomorrow's Saturday.

695
00:24:40,827 --> 00:24:43,660
From Wando to Jeju.

696
00:24:43,660 --> 00:24:44,577
[Here's the deal...]

697
00:24:44,577 --> 00:24:46,728
Travel dates.

698
00:24:46,728 --> 00:24:48,713
[See Ep 4, pre-dinner, at the lodging]
- We leave the morning of March 1st. - Yeah.

699
00:24:48,713 --> 00:24:50,281
- To Jeju.
- Yeah.

700
00:24:50,281 --> 00:24:53,219
[After 90 min of intense Jeju debate]

701
00:24:53,219 --> 00:24:56,150
If we want to go, we can just take a ferry.

702
00:24:56,150 --> 00:24:57,493
- Want me to look into ferries?
- It's really cheap.

703
00:24:57,493 --> 00:24:58,872
[They even check out ferries now...]
Huh? Ferry?

704
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:02,360
- Nokdong Port?
- Mokpo Port, Wando Port.

705
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:03,693
[However]
- It's tomorrow? - The 28th.

706
00:25:03,693 --> 00:25:06,097
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

707
00:25:06,097 --> 00:25:08,193
[Nokdong New Port OUT]

708
00:25:08,193 --> 00:25:09,592
- Details.
- One o'clock.

709
00:25:09,592 --> 00:25:11,560
[Mokpo Port ferry leaves at 1 AM]
We'd have to leave at one.

710
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,392
That's a bummer,
but it's really the case, right?

711
00:25:13,392 --> 00:25:15,493
[Only Wando Port is left now, but...]
We should've gone on day one.

712
00:25:15,493 --> 00:25:17,274
I'm hungry.

713
00:25:17,994 --> 00:25:19,612
[Forgot Wando, off to eat...]

714
00:25:19,612 --> 00:25:22,046
I need to eat something right now.

715
00:25:22,046 --> 00:25:25,049
[And so in the middle of the night]

716
00:25:25,049 --> 00:25:27,852
[The Jeju meeting opens back up]

717
00:25:27,852 --> 00:25:30,154
[Will there be Wando Port tickets?]
Booking for tomorrow.

718
00:25:30,154 --> 00:25:31,944
Checking.

719
00:25:31,944 --> 00:25:34,784
- Got one.
- 3 PM, yeah, there's one.

720
00:25:34,784 --> 00:25:37,044
- Got one.
- 3 PM, yeah, there's one.

721
00:25:37,044 --> 00:25:38,405
- Try that one.
- Looks like it works.

722
00:25:38,405 --> 00:25:41,132
- Yeah, there's one.
- Check how much.

723
00:25:41,132 --> 00:25:42,544
Third-class cabin.

724
00:25:42,544 --> 00:25:44,441
[Cheapest: third-class, 32,800 won per person]
That looks like the cheapest option.

725
00:25:44,441 --> 00:25:47,259
[Plenty of seats still open!]
There are tons of seats.

726
00:25:48,601 --> 00:25:51,241
[Going to Jeju tomorrow is doable!]
Yeah, there's a lot.

727
00:25:51,241 --> 00:25:54,361
But here's the problem.

728
00:25:54,361 --> 00:25:57,241
Let's think about this realistically.

729
00:25:57,241 --> 00:26:00,685
If we get to Jeju, how do we get out?

730
00:26:00,685 --> 00:26:02,286
[They looked up return flights, but...]

731
00:26:02,286 --> 00:26:03,601
Darn it.

732
00:26:03,601 --> 00:26:06,982
[All over 100k pp (feat. long holiday)]
- Hey, what's with this? - Scroll down.

733
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:08,359
I don't think we can make it back.

734
00:26:08,359 --> 00:26:10,393
Just...

735
00:26:10,393 --> 00:26:13,460
[Can get to Jeju, no way out...]
If we get to Jeju, how do we get out?

736
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:15,366
Let's leave one at a time.

737
00:26:16,560 --> 00:26:18,226
We'll have to fly back.

738
00:26:18,226 --> 00:26:19,726
We can't fly, the price.

739
00:26:19,726 --> 00:26:21,873
You head out first.

740
00:26:21,873 --> 00:26:24,293
Work first, whoever has work leaves quickly.

741
00:26:24,293 --> 00:26:26,293
I'll come back to rescue you!

742
00:26:26,293 --> 00:26:29,180
- And bring money from Seoul.
- Bring some money from Seoul.

743
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:31,117
[Willing to risk being stranded in Jeju]

744
00:26:31,117 --> 00:26:33,092
That's the only option!

745
00:26:33,092 --> 00:26:35,417
Let's just get there first.

746
00:26:35,417 --> 00:26:36,778
- Just go in?
- Yeah!

747
00:26:36,778 --> 00:26:39,338
If it doesn't work, we'll just ferry back out!

748
00:26:39,338 --> 00:26:40,992
So from Wando, back the way we came...

749
00:26:40,992 --> 00:26:44,959
and catch the KTX from there
and head up on March 1st.

750
00:26:44,959 --> 00:26:46,193
- Ugh, that's rough.
- For now...

751
00:26:46,193 --> 00:26:48,099
[A return route dizzying to imagine]
Look up the return ferry.

752
00:26:48,099 --> 00:26:51,159
Look up the return ferry.

753
00:26:51,159 --> 00:26:53,233
[Big sis getting bold]
But what if there isn't one...

754
00:26:53,233 --> 00:26:55,092
- The return?
- Oh, Lord.

755
00:26:55,092 --> 00:26:57,175
Is there one? Check the times.

756
00:26:57,175 --> 00:26:58,576
[Save us from this hell of options...]

757
00:26:58,576 --> 00:27:00,194
[Sigh]

758
00:27:00,194 --> 00:27:02,626
There are seats, plenty of them.

759
00:27:02,626 --> 00:27:05,193
- Okay.
- But the times...

760
00:27:05,193 --> 00:27:07,833
[What time's the ferry, exactly...]
Of course there's one.

761
00:27:09,253 --> 00:27:11,748
[Realistic option: the 4 PM ferry]

762
00:27:11,748 --> 00:27:14,359
- At four...
- We'll have to take the Gold Stella.

763
00:27:14,359 --> 00:27:15,873
If we leave at four, by six...

764
00:27:15,873 --> 00:27:18,738
we'll get to Wando around seven.

765
00:27:18,738 --> 00:27:23,968
From Wando to Seoul... once we arrive...

766
00:27:23,968 --> 00:27:28,007
Then there's the deluxe bus.

767
00:27:28,007 --> 00:27:30,974
So from Wando...

768
00:27:31,778 --> 00:27:33,811
From Wando...

769
00:27:38,216 --> 00:27:40,617
[Chat*PT]

770
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:45,426
Oh, Chat*PT again.

771
00:27:45,426 --> 00:27:48,526
What's the fastest way

772
00:27:48,526 --> 00:27:53,247
to get from Wando up to Seoul?

773
00:27:53,247 --> 00:27:57,435
Cheap would be nice.

774
00:27:57,435 --> 00:27:59,026
[Express bus: Wando to Seoul, 5hr, 40-60k won]

775
00:27:59,026 --> 00:28:01,159
Central City is right in Banpo.

776
00:28:01,159 --> 00:28:02,627
Five hours?

777
00:28:02,627 --> 00:28:04,808
Five hours isn't bad, right?

778
00:28:05,726 --> 00:28:08,330
[No...] [No...]

779
00:28:08,330 --> 00:28:11,626
This is 40 to 60k per person, right?

780
00:28:11,626 --> 00:28:14,352
We'd be traveling five hours straight

781
00:28:14,352 --> 00:28:18,026
with nothing to eat...

782
00:28:18,026 --> 00:28:20,526
[With ferry included, about eight hours]
three hours, eight hours total.

783
00:28:20,526 --> 00:28:23,560
But we get more money on March 1st.

784
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:27,165
But when you break it down,
it's six of one, half a dozen of the other.

785
00:28:27,165 --> 00:28:30,359
If you add 40 to 60k won plus the ferry fare...

786
00:28:30,359 --> 00:28:32,605
the flight is 100k won.

787
00:28:32,605 --> 00:28:34,426
- It's about the same.
- You're right.

788
00:28:34,426 --> 00:28:35,552
Price aside,

789
00:28:35,552 --> 00:28:39,226
[Back to square one again]
just in case there are no plane tickets.

790
00:28:39,226 --> 00:28:42,880
If not Jeju, let's pick somewhere else.

791
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:45,416
[Digging through the map again...]

792
00:28:45,416 --> 00:28:48,152
Sis, then close your eyes,
run over here, and pick a spot.

793
00:28:48,152 --> 00:28:49,238
[Day one tactic, activated]

794
00:28:49,238 --> 00:28:51,489
You go first. Hey, Seo Jun, you try first.

795
00:28:51,489 --> 00:28:53,126
Close your eyes and pick a spot.

796
00:28:53,126 --> 00:28:54,760
- You go first.
- You pick.

797
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:56,695
Let's all three of us try.

798
00:28:56,695 --> 00:28:59,055
Pick with your big toe instead.

799
00:28:59,055 --> 00:29:01,615
- All right, I'll do that. Hurry.
- For real?

800
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:03,095
Yeah, I'll do a side kick.

801
00:29:03,095 --> 00:29:05,234
Then I'll do it like this, watch.

802
00:29:05,234 --> 00:29:06,275
[Flexible]
I'll pick like this.

803
00:29:06,275 --> 00:29:07,334
All right.

804
00:29:07,334 --> 00:29:08,839
- Here I go.
- Okay.

805
00:29:08,839 --> 00:29:10,854
[Charging in with eyes closed]

806
00:29:10,854 --> 00:29:12,493
Hold on. No, not yet.

807
00:29:12,493 --> 00:29:13,755
- Here I go.
- Wait.

808
00:29:13,755 --> 00:29:16,180
- I'll set it up in front of you, hold on.
- That's the ocean.

809
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:17,327
[Korean Peninsula delivery]

810
00:29:17,327 --> 00:29:19,752
- Not there.
- What's this here?

811
00:29:19,752 --> 00:29:21,652
Where?

812
00:29:21,652 --> 00:29:23,365
Where's that?

813
00:29:23,365 --> 00:29:26,891
- This is Andong.
- Andong.

814
00:29:26,891 --> 00:29:28,193
Your turn.

815
00:29:28,193 --> 00:29:30,094
[Yumi's turn]
Me?

816
00:29:30,094 --> 00:29:32,440
- Go on, hurry.
- A back kick's never going to work.

817
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,519
If I go forward, I can see it like this.

818
00:29:34,519 --> 00:29:35,640
Close your eyes.

819
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:37,359
- Eyes closed?
- Yeah.

820
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:38,620
I don't think I can do it forward.

821
00:29:38,620 --> 00:29:40,039
Just pick.

822
00:29:40,039 --> 00:29:41,859
[Front kick fires]
Huh? What?

823
00:29:41,859 --> 00:29:44,408
- Huh? What?
- Daegu.

824
00:29:44,408 --> 00:29:46,377
[Kicked all that way, right back to that same place]
That's Daegu.

825
00:29:46,377 --> 00:29:48,200
- Again.
- A little higher.

826
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,800
- A little higher.
- Higher?

827
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,060
- Yeah.
- Higher?

828
00:29:51,060 --> 00:29:53,959
Hey, then you should pull it back
so all of Jeju shows.

829
00:29:53,959 --> 00:29:55,989
- You're trying to hit Jeju, aren't you?
- I'm not.

830
00:29:55,989 --> 00:29:57,090
[Jeju lover caught cheating]
Let me just try.

831
00:29:57,090 --> 00:30:00,405
- So I'm closing my eyes from here?
- Yeah.

832
00:30:00,405 --> 00:30:03,135
[Hyah!]
Where is it?

833
00:30:03,135 --> 00:30:04,662
Changwon!

834
00:30:04,662 --> 00:30:07,560
[Even at her best, she only got Gyeongsang-do]
I don't think this is right.

835
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,861
[Lastly, it's Woo Shik's turn]

836
00:30:08,861 --> 00:30:10,747
Try it with your eyes closed.

837
00:30:12,286 --> 00:30:14,914
[What will the final destination be?]
Hey, why are you pointing like that?

838
00:30:14,914 --> 00:30:17,421
- Kaesong...
- Kaesong?

839
00:30:18,070 --> 00:30:19,779
Ah, what do we do?

840
00:30:19,779 --> 00:30:22,425
[Blindfold destination challenge
ends empty-handed]

841
00:30:25,534 --> 00:30:28,426
At least we figured out
how to get to Jeju, right?

842
00:30:28,426 --> 00:30:29,761
[Positive Yumi]

843
00:30:30,543 --> 00:30:33,079
Seo Jun, what do you think about going to Jeju?

844
00:30:33,079 --> 00:30:35,254
It'll be tough, but if we're going,
we're going.

845
00:30:35,254 --> 00:30:36,451
Me too.

846
00:30:36,451 --> 00:30:37,877
Me too.

847
00:30:37,877 --> 00:30:40,025
[All we can see is Jeju...]
Then let's just go to Jeju.

848
00:30:40,025 --> 00:30:41,873
Then, let's just go to Jeju.

849
00:30:41,873 --> 00:30:43,734
Alright.

850
00:30:43,734 --> 00:30:46,889
- We'll find our way back somehow.
- We figured out how to get there too.

851
00:30:46,889 --> 00:30:48,742
[And so, eventually...]
I like Jeju Island.

852
00:30:48,742 --> 00:30:52,413
But first, let's focus on
getting to Wando Island.

853
00:30:52,413 --> 00:30:54,227
[Okay, Wando Port it is]
How are we supposed to find?

854
00:30:54,227 --> 00:30:57,487
- Wando Island.
- First of all, from Gwangju...

855
00:30:57,487 --> 00:30:59,920
Do you know what time that Tto*** Bakery opens?

856
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:03,195
We'd have to get up really early
to make it to the bakery.

857
00:31:03,195 --> 00:31:04,889
Then check what time it opens.

858
00:31:04,889 --> 00:31:07,714
[Lodging, Bakery, Terminal, Wando Port]
Jeju's gonna be rough.

859
00:31:07,714 --> 00:31:10,182
[Tto*** Bakery opens at 10 AM]
- Ten o'clock. - Ah, the timing's not great.

860
00:31:10,182 --> 00:31:11,781
They're in opposite directions, you know?

861
00:31:11,781 --> 00:31:13,318
- Exactly. It's in the opposite direction.
- Yeah.

862
00:31:13,318 --> 00:31:14,732
[The bakery and terminal are opposite ways]

863
00:31:14,732 --> 00:31:18,202
[Lodging, Tto*** Bakery, Gwangju Terminal,
30 minutes by subway]

864
00:31:18,202 --> 00:31:21,012
[Almost 1 hour just for travel time]

865
00:31:21,012 --> 00:31:24,891
Even if the bakery opens at 10 AM,
and we buy it right away,

866
00:31:24,891 --> 00:31:27,567
we can't make the 11:40 bus.

867
00:31:27,567 --> 00:31:29,880
But if we pick up the car tomorrow,
everything will be sorted out...

868
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,349
That's what I'm saying.

869
00:31:31,349 --> 00:31:33,918
We might as well just buy it here
and go up and come back down.

870
00:31:33,918 --> 00:31:35,698
[Since the cast members don't have phones,
the staff has to check in personally]

871
00:31:35,698 --> 00:31:37,385
- That's true.
- Are you in a meeting?

872
00:31:37,385 --> 00:31:38,666
We're in a meeting.

873
00:31:38,666 --> 00:31:40,667
- Oh, you were in a meeting?
- No, it's okay.

874
00:31:40,667 --> 00:31:43,028
What time do we have to wake up tomorrow?

875
00:31:43,028 --> 00:31:45,141
Then we have to do it by 9 AM.

876
00:31:45,141 --> 00:31:47,677
[Suggestion: do the benefit draw at 9 AM]
- The draw? - Yeah.

877
00:31:47,677 --> 00:31:48,994
Why 9 o'clock?

878
00:31:48,994 --> 00:31:51,610
Because we're going by the bakery's schedule.

879
00:31:51,610 --> 00:31:53,940
You think it'll be over that quickly?

880
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:57,244
If we take our time,
we'll leave around 9:30 AM.

881
00:31:57,244 --> 00:32:00,780
- So we get there before 10 AM.
- We need to do an opening run.

882
00:32:00,780 --> 00:32:02,680
- The thing is, we have to wait in line there.
- We have to wait in line.

883
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,984
If we don't go when they open,
we'll wait in line and get nothing.

884
00:32:04,984 --> 00:32:07,133
The line will be too long.

885
00:32:07,133 --> 00:32:09,172
If we can't get the car,
we'll just head straight for Wando Island.

886
00:32:09,172 --> 00:32:10,588
- Right.
- Yeah.

887
00:32:10,588 --> 00:32:12,775
- The allowance drop and raffle at 9:00 AM?
- Yes.

888
00:32:12,775 --> 00:32:14,977
- And leave at 9:30 AM?
- Yes.

889
00:32:14,977 --> 00:32:17,043
[Mutual agreement on call time achieved]
If we get the car...

890
00:32:17,043 --> 00:32:19,629
Ah, it's already around 12:30.

891
00:32:19,629 --> 00:32:21,001
[The second meeting went over an hour]
We really need to get to bed.

892
00:32:21,001 --> 00:32:22,889
Let's go to bed early.

893
00:32:22,889 --> 00:32:24,270
Guys, see you tomorrow!

894
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:26,071
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

895
00:32:26,071 --> 00:32:27,887
We're going to Jeju!

896
00:32:27,887 --> 00:32:30,584
[Just when the night seemed to be ending...]

897
00:32:31,871 --> 00:32:33,726
Writer, can we talk for a second?

898
00:32:33,726 --> 00:32:35,132
[The staff meeting is only beginning]

899
00:32:35,132 --> 00:32:38,482
I mean, taking the ferry there is fine, but...

900
00:32:38,482 --> 00:32:42,521
[Holiday flights to Gimpo are sold out]
Even we can't get tickets now.

901
00:32:42,521 --> 00:32:43,869
But what's going on right now?

902
00:32:43,869 --> 00:32:46,657
I was getting nonstop messages earlier.

903
00:32:46,657 --> 00:32:49,834
[While the trio met,
the staff desperately searched for tickets]

904
00:32:49,834 --> 00:32:51,571
[And then...]

905
00:32:51,571 --> 00:32:53,130
[What about the morning flight?]

906
00:32:53,130 --> 00:32:54,658
[As*** Airlines has a 7:10 AM flight]

907
00:32:54,658 --> 00:32:55,920
[Then that's the latest flight, right?]

908
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:58,727
[They found exactly one available flight]

909
00:32:58,727 --> 00:33:02,306
We can all get seats
on the March 1st Asi*** flight...

910
00:33:02,306 --> 00:33:03,667
Wow, really?

911
00:33:03,667 --> 00:33:05,399
But we'll need some business seats.

912
00:33:05,399 --> 00:33:07,812
[Somehow, the spontaneous Jeju shoot prep
goes surprisingly smoothly]

913
00:33:07,812 --> 00:33:10,878
[And so, the Jeju planning hell
continued all night...]

914
00:33:11,782 --> 00:33:14,726
[Before they knew it, Jeju D-day had arrived]

915
00:33:15,492 --> 00:33:19,851
[7:00 AM, Seo Jun &amp; Woo Shik's room]

916
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:25,178
[Seo Jun wakes up first]

917
00:33:28,513 --> 00:33:30,495
[Before the big day begins...]

918
00:33:30,495 --> 00:33:34,419
[Facing the morning with solemn determination]

919
00:33:35,473 --> 00:33:37,617
[Yumi wakes up second]

920
00:33:39,346 --> 00:33:43,421
[Yumi also starts warming up]

921
00:33:43,421 --> 00:33:45,407
[Ready to face the world]

922
00:33:52,647 --> 00:33:54,973
[But the world is still cold]

923
00:33:54,973 --> 00:33:57,176
[Wobble...]

924
00:33:59,159 --> 00:34:01,098
Are you awake?

925
00:34:01,098 --> 00:34:02,412
Huh? He's not here.

926
00:34:02,412 --> 00:34:04,470
[No]

927
00:34:04,470 --> 00:34:05,832
- Woo Shik.
- Huh?

928
00:34:05,832 --> 00:34:06,926
Are you awake?

929
00:34:06,926 --> 00:34:08,887
- What time is it?
- Seo Jun's gone.

930
00:34:08,887 --> 00:34:10,774
[Lastly, the youngest wakes up]

931
00:34:10,774 --> 00:34:14,127
- Yeah.
- This battery is dead. Ugh!

932
00:34:14,127 --> 00:34:17,824
[Two head bumps achieved in one minute]

933
00:34:17,824 --> 00:34:20,587
- Are you okay?
- It hurts.

934
00:34:20,587 --> 00:34:23,697
- What time is it now?
- Ah, I don't know.

935
00:34:23,697 --> 00:34:26,912
- This thing's battery died.
- Ah, really?

936
00:34:26,912 --> 00:34:28,424
- Yumi.
- Yeah?

937
00:34:28,424 --> 00:34:31,996
- I'll leave this laptop in the living room.
- Yeah.

938
00:34:31,996 --> 00:34:34,874
[Back to laptop alarms without phones]
Use this to wake up, okay?

939
00:34:34,874 --> 00:34:36,896
Ah, then set mine for 7:50 AM.

940
00:34:36,896 --> 00:34:39,825
[They had set a 7:50 alarm on the laptop...]
- 7:50 AM? - Yeah.

941
00:34:39,825 --> 00:34:41,707
Yeah, this thing was off.

942
00:34:41,707 --> 00:34:44,194
[They somehow woke up by instinct]
- Really? - Yeah.

943
00:34:45,099 --> 00:34:47,519
[Computer ON]

944
00:34:47,519 --> 00:34:49,413
It's 8 o'clock.

945
00:34:49,413 --> 00:34:51,221
[1 hour before the benefit draw]
- It's 8 o'clock? - Yeah.

946
00:34:51,221 --> 00:34:53,893
- Exactly 8 o'clock?
- Yeah, 8:04 AM.

947
00:34:57,762 --> 00:34:59,676
Today, we absolutely...

948
00:35:01,545 --> 00:35:03,889
have to win the car.

949
00:35:03,889 --> 00:35:06,551
[Serious]

950
00:35:07,308 --> 00:35:11,237
[Etching their wishes into the camcorder...]

951
00:35:11,237 --> 00:35:13,971
[Ten minutes before the benefit draw]

952
00:35:13,971 --> 00:35:17,556
[Tension fills the room...]

953
00:35:17,556 --> 00:35:20,059
Why aren't these people coming?

954
00:35:20,059 --> 00:35:22,507
Why aren't they coming?

955
00:35:22,507 --> 00:35:24,264
Why aren't they coming?

956
00:35:24,264 --> 00:35:27,990
[The staff scheduled for 9:00 hasn't arrived]
- Why aren't they here? - Hurry over.

957
00:35:28,579 --> 00:35:31,023
[Five minutes before the benefit draw]

958
00:35:31,023 --> 00:35:33,465
Seriously, where is everybody?

959
00:35:33,465 --> 00:35:34,587
[They only grow more anxious...]

960
00:35:34,587 --> 00:35:36,962
Are we not filming today?

961
00:35:36,962 --> 00:35:38,564
[9:00 AM]

962
00:35:38,564 --> 00:35:41,050
Are we not filming today?

963
00:35:41,050 --> 00:35:42,143
Ah, seriously.

964
00:35:42,143 --> 00:35:43,469
[The staff is late...]

965
00:35:43,469 --> 00:35:46,005
[9:05 AM]
I literally just woke up.

966
00:35:46,005 --> 00:35:48,235
[Beep, beep]

967
00:35:48,235 --> 00:35:50,574
They're here.

968
00:35:50,574 --> 00:35:52,015
- Sorry.
- What are you doing?

969
00:35:52,015 --> 00:35:53,749
Why are you late?

970
00:35:53,749 --> 00:35:56,195
- Ah, we need to go.
- We told you, we need to buy the bread.

971
00:35:56,195 --> 00:35:57,824
[Restless]
Sorry.

972
00:35:57,824 --> 00:35:59,123
We didn't realize it got this late.

973
00:35:59,123 --> 00:36:03,369
I even woke up early and went for a walk.

974
00:36:03,369 --> 00:36:06,734
Alright, where should we start?

975
00:36:06,734 --> 00:36:08,222
Ah...

976
00:36:08,222 --> 00:36:11,289
[The fateful benefit draw]
- The final draw of fate. - Please!

977
00:36:11,289 --> 00:36:12,986
Oh, please.

978
00:36:12,986 --> 00:36:16,381
- We'll give you your allowance first.
- Quickly, quickly.

979
00:36:16,381 --> 00:36:18,211
- The allowance is over there.
- 100,000 won per person.

980
00:36:18,211 --> 00:36:20,542
[300,000 won allowance]
Don't you still have a lot of allowance left?

981
00:36:20,542 --> 00:36:23,209
We still have about 80,000 won left.

982
00:36:23,209 --> 00:36:25,481
One, two, three, four, five, six...

983
00:36:25,481 --> 00:36:26,851
65,000 won.

984
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:29,160
Total 365,000 won.

985
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,146
Just touch it, just once.

986
00:36:32,146 --> 00:36:33,586
- Oh, please...
- Please.

987
00:36:33,586 --> 00:36:36,253
[Trying to absorb some car luck]
- Please. - Ah, please.

988
00:36:36,253 --> 00:36:39,271
- Wait a second. You better come, okay?
- Touch it a little.

989
00:36:39,271 --> 00:36:41,120
- You absolutely have to come.
- Seo Jun, touch this too.

990
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:43,969
You guys go away. You have to come, okay?

991
00:36:43,969 --> 00:36:46,892
[Car... you know how I feel, right?]
- Please come. You know, right? - Please.

992
00:36:46,892 --> 00:36:48,769
[The staff is just as nervous...]
Ah, please...

993
00:36:48,769 --> 00:36:50,909
Please just pick it already. For us too.

994
00:36:50,909 --> 00:36:52,986
[We survive only if you guys have it easy...]

995
00:36:52,986 --> 00:36:55,121
[The dice of fate have been cast]

996
00:36:55,121 --> 00:36:57,696
Ah, this is driving me crazy.

997
00:36:57,696 --> 00:36:59,404
- Let's do rock-paper-scissors.
- I want to film this.

998
00:36:59,404 --> 00:37:00,439
The winner should draw.

999
00:37:00,439 --> 00:37:03,881
No matter what comes out,
we don't blame each other.

1000
00:37:03,881 --> 00:37:07,219
- We don't blame each other. Got it?
- I won't blame anyone.

1001
00:37:07,219 --> 00:37:09,520
[Who will be today's pick in the draw?]
- Rock-paper-scissors... - Winner goes.

1002
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:10,572
Wait, wait, wait.

1003
00:37:10,572 --> 00:37:12,437
- The winner draws it?
- The winner draws it.

1004
00:37:12,437 --> 00:37:13,649
The winner has good luck.

1005
00:37:13,649 --> 00:37:16,281
- Rock-paper-scissors!
- Rock-paper-scissors!

1006
00:37:16,281 --> 00:37:17,947
[Woo Shik loses]

1007
00:37:17,947 --> 00:37:19,049
[Yes!]

1008
00:37:19,049 --> 00:37:20,661
[Hopeless...]

1009
00:37:20,661 --> 00:37:22,521
Ah, this is a bomb.

1010
00:37:22,521 --> 00:37:24,213
Rock-paper-scissors!

1011
00:37:24,213 --> 00:37:26,475
[Park Seo Jun wins]

1012
00:37:26,475 --> 00:37:28,430
[We survived!]

1013
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:31,384
[Ughhhhh]

1014
00:37:31,384 --> 00:37:32,501
[Today's benefit picker: Park Seo Jun]

1015
00:37:32,501 --> 00:37:34,079
This pressure...

1016
00:37:34,079 --> 00:37:35,962
Don't hesitate, just go right in.

1017
00:37:35,962 --> 00:37:36,987
Just go right in.

1018
00:37:36,987 --> 00:37:39,785
[Trust Seo Jun's luck now]
I aligned my body clock this morning?

1019
00:37:39,785 --> 00:37:41,740
Don't think about it.
If you grabbed one, just pull it out.

1020
00:37:41,740 --> 00:37:42,846
I got one.

1021
00:37:42,846 --> 00:37:44,455
- This is really hard to watch.
- I really can't watch this.

1022
00:37:44,455 --> 00:37:46,890
[What benefit will decide today's fate?]
- Did you pull it out? - Yeah, he did.

1023
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:48,268
Or...

1024
00:37:48,268 --> 00:37:51,922
- My hands are shaking right now.
- Or instead...

1025
00:37:51,922 --> 00:37:53,960
Should we open them one by one?

1026
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:57,022
- Huh?
- Yeah, let's do that.

1027
00:37:57,868 --> 00:38:00,142
Please...

1028
00:38:00,142 --> 00:38:03,332
Please, please...

1029
00:38:03,332 --> 00:38:04,612
[He picked one]
Just open that one.

1030
00:38:04,612 --> 00:38:07,353
My hands are sweaty right now.

1031
00:38:07,353 --> 00:38:09,926
I hope we at least get that one, please...

1032
00:38:11,764 --> 00:38:12,804
Oh! Lodging.

1033
00:38:12,804 --> 00:38:14,180
[Lodging OUT]

1034
00:38:14,180 --> 00:38:16,211
[Only the phone and car remain]
Wait. Oh!

1035
00:38:16,211 --> 00:38:17,305
[Eureka]

1036
00:38:17,305 --> 00:38:19,991
- Seriously.
- Oh, wait...

1037
00:38:20,927 --> 00:38:23,203
[Complete chaos]

1038
00:38:23,203 --> 00:38:25,971
[Even the staff is freaking out]
Ah, wait, wait...

1039
00:38:25,971 --> 00:38:27,525
It's all or nothing.

1040
00:38:27,525 --> 00:38:29,358
It's all or nothing.

1041
00:38:30,899 --> 00:38:32,003
[Sneak peek]

1042
00:38:34,698 --> 00:38:37,004
- Did you see it?
- I don't know, he saw it.

1043
00:38:37,004 --> 00:38:38,098
What is it?

1044
00:38:38,098 --> 00:38:39,423
[Sigh]

1045
00:38:43,995 --> 00:38:46,579
- Darn it!
- Let me see.

1046
00:38:46,579 --> 00:38:48,541
- Okay, let me see.
- Come on.

1047
00:38:48,541 --> 00:38:49,826
You guys are really good at acting.

1048
00:38:49,826 --> 00:38:52,658
[Is this reaction acting or real?]
- Let me see. - Come on.

1049
00:38:52,658 --> 00:38:54,806
No, it can't be.

1050
00:38:56,627 --> 00:38:58,401
- We're screwed.
- No, no.

1051
00:38:58,401 --> 00:38:59,875
[Real]

1052
00:38:59,875 --> 00:39:01,233
No, no. Wait a second.

1053
00:39:01,233 --> 00:39:03,333
- We'll only look once. Hurry.
- Seo Jun, that's not it...

1054
00:39:03,333 --> 00:39:05,721
- That's not it...
- I'm going to slate it.

1055
00:39:05,721 --> 00:39:08,828
- Slate it.
- You know what?

1056
00:39:13,208 --> 00:39:15,478
[The reality is too harsh to accept]
Quickly, quickly!

1057
00:39:15,478 --> 00:39:19,529
- Sorry, but you need to reveal it quickly.
- You need to reveal it already...

1058
00:39:19,529 --> 00:39:21,654
But wait, time out.

1059
00:39:22,381 --> 00:39:24,542
[Desperately trying to create an editing point]
Wait, wait!

1060
00:39:24,542 --> 00:39:26,223
Just wait.

1061
00:39:26,223 --> 00:39:28,867
[Originally...]
Wasn't this one a little thicker?

1062
00:39:30,327 --> 00:39:31,995
[Ridiculous]

1063
00:39:31,995 --> 00:39:33,463
What are you talking about?

1064
00:39:33,463 --> 00:39:35,766
[Clinging to false hope until the very end]
Wasn't it originally a little thicker?

1065
00:39:35,766 --> 00:39:39,620
No way... did you just draw the phone...

1066
00:39:40,416 --> 00:39:43,675
[A silence that confirms the worst...]

1067
00:39:45,709 --> 00:39:48,701
So, you picked a phone, Mr. Park Seo Jun?

1068
00:39:48,701 --> 00:39:50,794
We actually didn't see it.

1069
00:39:50,794 --> 00:39:52,883
But still, I shouldn't lie.

1070
00:39:52,883 --> 00:39:56,186
That little "hieut" really felt like
it was mocking me.

1071
00:39:56,186 --> 00:39:57,521
I really did.

1072
00:39:57,521 --> 00:40:03,106
Wow, it's been a long time
since I got this mad at a piece of paper.

1073
00:40:03,746 --> 00:40:06,129
It was completely hopeless...

1074
00:40:06,129 --> 00:40:08,968
Anyway, each of us ended up picking a phone.

1075
00:40:08,968 --> 00:40:13,003
Ironically, it was the day we least
needed phones, you know?

1076
00:40:13,003 --> 00:40:15,517
But somehow, he ended up
picking a phone anyway...

1077
00:40:15,517 --> 00:40:17,380
Honestly, my mind just went blank then.

1078
00:40:17,380 --> 00:40:19,141
What are we supposed to do now?

1079
00:40:19,141 --> 00:40:21,273
So then...

1080
00:40:21,273 --> 00:40:24,123
we made a deal.

1081
00:40:24,123 --> 00:40:26,304
Would you like to try the draw again
using the allowance

1082
00:40:26,304 --> 00:40:27,584
[Pay to retry?]
you had left from yesterday?

1083
00:40:27,584 --> 00:40:29,152
For 65,000 won?

1084
00:40:29,152 --> 00:40:30,787
- Let's do it.
- But it might be worth a shot, right?

1085
00:40:30,787 --> 00:40:32,155
Yeah, 65,000 won...

1086
00:40:32,155 --> 00:40:35,469
Instead, if you draw the phone again,
you'd only lose 65,000 won.

1087
00:40:35,469 --> 00:40:37,861
- Ah, it's okay. Let's try once.
- I think we should try again.

1088
00:40:37,861 --> 00:40:39,630
[Even if we fail, just GO]
- Yeah, 65,000 won. - Ah, this isn't it.

1089
00:40:39,630 --> 00:40:42,332
[Strongly in favor]
- Are you in favor? - I'm in favor.

1090
00:40:42,332 --> 00:40:44,214
[Will they draw the car with 65,000 won?]
I'm in.

1091
00:40:44,214 --> 00:40:46,162
It might not come out at all.

1092
00:40:46,162 --> 00:40:47,855
- I'll draw it.
- Yeah.

1093
00:40:47,855 --> 00:40:49,139
- I'll draw it.
- Yeah.

1094
00:40:49,139 --> 00:40:50,595
[This time, Woo Shik will draw]
- I'll draw it. - Okay.

1095
00:40:50,595 --> 00:40:53,336
Here you go. Giving us one more chance?

1096
00:40:53,944 --> 00:40:55,554
- Please shake this once for us.
- Yeah.

1097
00:40:55,554 --> 00:40:57,211
Please, please!

1098
00:40:57,211 --> 00:40:58,213
Alright.

1099
00:40:58,213 --> 00:40:59,911
[The wheel of fate spins once again...]

1100
00:40:59,911 --> 00:41:01,377
The time is...

1101
00:41:01,377 --> 00:41:03,921
- What time is it now, though?
- It's almost 9:30 now.

1102
00:41:03,921 --> 00:41:05,656
We'll have to leave right after this draw.

1103
00:41:05,656 --> 00:41:08,067
- I seriously won't blame you.
- Yeah.

1104
00:41:08,856 --> 00:41:10,333
[He picked one]

1105
00:41:11,616 --> 00:41:13,631
[Please!]

1106
00:41:16,998 --> 00:41:18,521
- Oh, please...
- Hey...

1107
00:41:18,521 --> 00:41:19,922
Please!

1108
00:41:19,922 --> 00:41:23,208
- Should I just open it right away?
- No, no, just a little.

1109
00:41:23,208 --> 00:41:26,274
- Good, good.
- Good?

1110
00:41:27,177 --> 00:41:29,809
- Open it all the way. I still can't see it.
- Nothing yet... nothing at all.

1111
00:41:29,809 --> 00:41:31,615
Oh, why isn't it showing?

1112
00:41:31,615 --> 00:41:33,748
Hey, I don't think it's three letters.

1113
00:41:33,748 --> 00:41:35,285
Not three letters.

1114
00:41:35,285 --> 00:41:38,355
- Wait. Good, good. Huh?
- Wait...

1115
00:41:38,355 --> 00:41:40,668
- Huh? Wait.
- Good, good.

1116
00:41:40,668 --> 00:41:42,354
- What is this?
- I think... wait.

1117
00:41:42,354 --> 00:41:43,594
Hey,

1118
00:41:43,594 --> 00:41:45,696
this kinda looks like "chieut," doesn't it?

1119
00:41:45,696 --> 00:41:47,664
- It's lodging.
- Looks like the "so" character.

1120
00:41:47,664 --> 00:41:50,019
It's probably not it, right?

1121
00:41:51,335 --> 00:41:52,883
Go a little further.

1122
00:42:00,716 --> 00:42:02,412
[Won the car]

1123
00:42:02,412 --> 00:42:05,024
[Can't believe it]

1124
00:42:10,028 --> 00:42:12,260
[Car, double confirmation]

1125
00:42:14,925 --> 00:42:16,695
[So happy]

1126
00:42:17,856 --> 00:42:20,297
[We're happy too]

1127
00:42:20,297 --> 00:42:23,567
[It's a festival now!]

1128
00:42:23,567 --> 00:42:26,503
[That's my boy]

1129
00:42:26,503 --> 00:42:29,406
[Without a doubt, today's MVP: Choi Woo Shik]

1130
00:42:29,406 --> 00:42:31,475
Hey, good deal, good deal!

1131
00:42:31,475 --> 00:42:34,211
[The best choice that saved everyone!]
Good deal!

1132
00:42:34,211 --> 00:42:36,646
[The lingering emotion...]

1133
00:42:36,646 --> 00:42:39,139
I don't remember that short moment.

1134
00:42:39,139 --> 00:42:43,053
Because during that short moment,
Yumi ended up on top of me...

1135
00:42:43,053 --> 00:42:47,025
Nobody even pushed her,
so I don't know why she was crushing me.

1136
00:42:47,025 --> 00:42:51,277
So I felt kinda suffocated, but anyway,
it was amazing.

1137
00:42:51,277 --> 00:42:55,665
My dopamine was shooting
all the way up to here.

1138
00:42:55,665 --> 00:42:57,308
Wow, at that moment...

1139
00:42:57,308 --> 00:43:02,072
I think I could honestly rank
that as one of the best moments of the trip.

1140
00:43:02,072 --> 00:43:04,851
Writer Su Kyeong and Producer Geon Jun...

1141
00:43:04,851 --> 00:43:07,077
from what I've seen recently,

1142
00:43:07,077 --> 00:43:10,614
I think they were honestly as happy as we were,
maybe even happier.

1143
00:43:10,614 --> 00:43:12,968
No, no, I think they were happier than we.

1144
00:43:12,968 --> 00:43:15,352
We were basically one team at that point.

1145
00:43:15,352 --> 00:43:18,274
Because Woo Shik drew it,
we got to use a car for the first time.

1146
00:43:18,274 --> 00:43:21,093
- Ah!
- Us too...

1147
00:43:22,710 --> 00:43:24,404
Then shall we leave right away?

1148
00:43:24,404 --> 00:43:26,426
[Let's go!]
- Let's go buy bread. - To the bakery.

1149
00:43:26,426 --> 00:43:28,358
Alright then, what's the plan?

1150
00:43:28,358 --> 00:43:29,579
First, the bakery.

1151
00:43:29,579 --> 00:43:31,074
- We'll go to the bakery first.
- Yeah.

1152
00:43:31,074 --> 00:43:32,836
- Then Wando Island.
- Then we'll go to Wando Island.

1153
00:43:32,836 --> 00:43:34,867
We'll load the car and head to Jeju!

1154
00:43:34,867 --> 00:43:36,776
Yeah!

1155
00:43:36,776 --> 00:43:41,078
[Finally, the dream Jeju trip begins!]

1156
00:43:41,078 --> 00:43:44,214
[The car is ready, so please come down]

1157
00:43:44,214 --> 00:43:45,715
Oh, yeah!

1158
00:43:45,715 --> 00:43:47,184
- Let's go to the bakery.
- Let's head to the bakery first.

1159
00:43:47,184 --> 00:43:48,888
Let's get in first.

1160
00:43:49,883 --> 00:43:52,055
[First, load the luggage into the trunk]

1161
00:43:52,055 --> 00:43:54,760
[Start the engine, vroom]

1162
00:43:55,378 --> 00:43:56,642
Tto*** Bakery.

1163
00:43:56,642 --> 00:43:58,917
[They enter "Tto*** Bakery"
into the navigation]

1164
00:43:59,799 --> 00:44:01,725
[Close the trunk]

1165
00:44:03,185 --> 00:44:05,168
[Once Woo Shik gets in too]

1166
00:44:05,168 --> 00:44:06,992
- Shall we go?
- Wow.

1167
00:44:06,992 --> 00:44:08,906
Let's go!

1168
00:44:10,478 --> 00:44:12,639
We finally got it.

1169
00:44:12,639 --> 00:44:13,910
Seriously...

1170
00:44:13,910 --> 00:44:15,988
Feels like a storm just swept through.

1171
00:44:15,988 --> 00:44:18,876
[Attention everyone, we have a car today]
Ah, I lost my voice.

1172
00:44:18,876 --> 00:44:20,399
Wow, that's such a relief.

1173
00:44:20,399 --> 00:44:21,535
Huh? Yeah.

1174
00:44:21,535 --> 00:44:23,616
That was seriously a good deal.

1175
00:44:24,310 --> 00:44:27,557
- Still, 65,000 won was kinda steep, right?
- Yeah.

1176
00:44:27,557 --> 00:44:30,017
But considering Jeju rental car prices...

1177
00:44:30,017 --> 00:44:31,610
- totally worth it.
- Ah, it's still a win.

1178
00:44:31,610 --> 00:44:32,977
Yeah.

1179
00:44:33,924 --> 00:44:34,965
[Whips the hat off]

1180
00:44:34,965 --> 00:44:37,636
- Yumi, are you gonna wear a hat today or not?
- I'm not gonna wear one, you can.

1181
00:44:37,636 --> 00:44:41,048
- Then can I wear that cap from earlier?
- Yeah, go ahead and wear it.

1182
00:44:41,048 --> 00:44:42,987
[The blue bucket hat also belonged to Yumi]

1183
00:44:42,987 --> 00:44:45,008
- What, are you worried it'll smell?
- No.

1184
00:44:45,008 --> 00:44:46,409
- Because it's kinda big?
- No.

1185
00:44:46,409 --> 00:44:48,107
This one's gonna smell too if I wear it.

1186
00:44:48,107 --> 00:44:49,848
Ah, I don't care.

1187
00:44:49,848 --> 00:44:51,815
- We can just send it to the cleaners.
- I'll pay the dry-cleaning fee.

1188
00:44:51,815 --> 00:44:55,218
[Kind Yumi lending her hat]
No, stop lying.

1189
00:44:55,218 --> 00:44:58,021
So we're taking the ferry together
with this car?

1190
00:44:58,021 --> 00:44:59,923
- Right.
- Okay.

1191
00:44:59,923 --> 00:45:02,952
Ah, but in Jeju, you really need a car.

1192
00:45:02,952 --> 00:45:05,362
What do you want to eat in Jeju?

1193
00:45:05,362 --> 00:45:07,793
Can't we have braised cutlassfish for lunch?

1194
00:45:07,793 --> 00:45:10,467
We can't have lunch.
We're arriving in the evening.

1195
00:45:10,467 --> 00:45:12,502
[Blank stare]

1196
00:45:12,502 --> 00:45:14,787
Oh, you're right.

1197
00:45:14,787 --> 00:45:17,240
What do you want to eat most in Jeju?

1198
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:19,943
- For me, black pork.
- Black pork?

1199
00:45:19,943 --> 00:45:21,745
What about you, Yumi?

1200
00:45:21,745 --> 00:45:23,085
[Neutral stance]
I'm...

1201
00:45:23,085 --> 00:45:26,475
I'm good with either
braised cutlassfish or black pork.

1202
00:45:26,475 --> 00:45:28,302
Or...

1203
00:45:29,078 --> 00:45:31,154
should we eat both?

1204
00:45:31,154 --> 00:45:33,450
A little here, a little there.

1205
00:45:35,170 --> 00:45:37,160
[A suffocating silence]

1206
00:45:37,160 --> 00:45:38,828
Oh, right. We don't have lodging, do we?

1207
00:45:38,828 --> 00:45:42,098
[Trying to indirectly say they're broke]
Yeah. We still need to book a place too.

1208
00:45:42,098 --> 00:45:44,659
We should book the lodging first before we eat.

1209
00:45:44,659 --> 00:45:47,669
- With whatever money is left, right?
- Since it'll be late.

1210
00:45:47,669 --> 00:45:50,480
[Thankfully, back to reality]
Because we have to eat with what's left.

1211
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:53,070
Huh? That's a poop truck.

1212
00:45:53,070 --> 00:45:54,878
A poop truck?

1213
00:45:54,878 --> 00:45:57,438
- They say seeing a poop truck means good luck.
- Really?

1214
00:45:57,438 --> 00:45:59,507
[Fun fact: Seeing a sewage truck
is said to bring good luck]

1215
00:45:59,507 --> 00:46:03,662
- People used to say that when I was little.
- Guess we're lucky today.

1216
00:46:03,662 --> 00:46:06,790
It would be even better
if we saw one or two more.

1217
00:46:06,790 --> 00:46:08,484
[At the time, they didn't know]

1218
00:46:08,484 --> 00:46:09,593
Oh, that's a poop truck?

1219
00:46:09,593 --> 00:46:11,320
That color's usually green and blue...

1220
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:12,784
[the mystical power of the poop truck]

1221
00:46:12,784 --> 00:46:13,785
Really?

1222
00:46:13,785 --> 00:46:15,765
[Falling over]

1223
00:46:15,765 --> 00:46:17,934
[Getting back up]

1224
00:46:17,934 --> 00:46:20,485
[Dancing]

1225
00:46:20,485 --> 00:46:22,272
[Clutching their hearts]

1226
00:46:22,272 --> 00:46:24,165
[The poop truck's butterfly effect
that triggered a storm]

1227
00:46:24,165 --> 00:46:25,928
- Is this right?
- This is it.

1228
00:46:25,928 --> 00:46:28,778
Something's definitely happening today
after seeing that poop truck.

1229
00:46:28,778 --> 00:46:30,788
[Ten minutes before arriving at Tto*** Bakery]

1230
00:46:31,688 --> 00:46:33,516
Do you think the line will be long?

1231
00:46:33,516 --> 00:46:35,945
- Yeah, since it's Saturday.
- I think so.

1232
00:46:35,945 --> 00:46:38,295
What if that old guy's there again?

1233
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:41,198
It'd be hilarious if he were here.

1234
00:46:41,198 --> 00:46:43,580
Man, I wanna eat the corn bread already.

1235
00:46:43,580 --> 00:46:45,809
- Blueberry bread is also said to be good.
- Yeah.

1236
00:46:45,809 --> 00:46:48,525
[The model student already studied via Shorts]
They've got chocolate bread too.

1237
00:46:48,525 --> 00:46:51,234
- We'll be able to buy some, right?
- Yeah.

1238
00:46:52,821 --> 00:46:55,305
[The Tto*** Bakery the trio is heading to...]

1239
00:46:55,305 --> 00:46:57,035
[Bread comes out at 10:00, 10:40,
12:00, 12:40, 1:20, 1:53, 14:50, 3:25]

1240
00:46:57,035 --> 00:46:59,743
[Fresh bread comes out multiple times a day]

1241
00:46:59,743 --> 00:47:01,144
[The time the trio is aiming for is...]

1242
00:47:01,144 --> 00:47:04,414
[Open-run at 10 AM]

1243
00:47:04,414 --> 00:47:06,894
[It's especially crowded on weekends like this]

1244
00:47:06,894 --> 00:47:08,573
Why is the traffic jammed?

1245
00:47:08,573 --> 00:47:11,037
Making people all anxious.

1246
00:47:11,037 --> 00:47:13,623
[Tto*** Bakery, five minutes before opening]

1247
00:47:13,623 --> 00:47:15,659
- Get ready to get out first.
- Alright, get ready to get out.

1248
00:47:15,659 --> 00:47:17,247
[Tto*** Bakery, two minutes before opening]

1249
00:47:17,247 --> 00:47:18,933
Let's go.

1250
00:47:18,933 --> 00:47:21,834
Oh! That's the one we saw in the pictures.

1251
00:47:21,834 --> 00:47:25,068
If parking's tight,
do you want to line up first?

1252
00:47:25,068 --> 00:47:26,540
- Oh, here it is!
- Here it is!

1253
00:47:26,540 --> 00:47:29,058
Oh, people are already gathered.

1254
00:47:29,058 --> 00:47:31,480
Hey, get in line.

1255
00:47:31,480 --> 00:47:34,244
[Seo Jun will park and join them]

1256
00:47:34,244 --> 00:47:36,946
[Tto*** Bakery opens the moment they arrive]

1257
00:47:36,946 --> 00:47:39,015
[Waiting Team 1, Waiting Team 2]

1258
00:47:39,015 --> 00:47:41,318
[Thankfully, the line isn't long]
Man, the bread smells insane.

1259
00:47:41,318 --> 00:47:43,389
We're finally here!

1260
00:47:43,389 --> 00:47:46,189
[Seo Jun arrives after parking]

1261
00:47:46,189 --> 00:47:47,630
[Excitedly tapping their feet]

1262
00:47:47,630 --> 00:47:50,275
Tto*** Bakery makes you wanna come back again.

1263
00:47:50,951 --> 00:47:53,129
The smell of the bread is no joke.

1264
00:47:53,129 --> 00:47:54,478
The blueberry one is out.

1265
00:47:54,478 --> 00:47:58,276
- Let's get the one the old man recommended.
- Yeah, that one.

1266
00:47:59,863 --> 00:48:02,463
[Grandpa Teto's pick: garlic bread]

1267
00:48:03,406 --> 00:48:06,528
[Woo Shik's anticipated pick: blueberry bread]

1268
00:48:06,528 --> 00:48:08,174
[The breads arrive in the tray and all]

1269
00:48:08,174 --> 00:48:11,434
- Whoa, what's that?
- It's corn bread.

1270
00:48:11,434 --> 00:48:14,083
Man, I want to buy everything,
but do we even have enough money?

1271
00:48:14,083 --> 00:48:15,690
[Shaking eyes]

1272
00:48:15,690 --> 00:48:17,053
- Let's buy exactly three.
- Let's just buy three.

1273
00:48:17,053 --> 00:48:18,702
Chocolate, corn, and blueberry bread.

1274
00:48:18,702 --> 00:48:20,816
[Still lingering with regret]
But the old guy said...

1275
00:48:20,816 --> 00:48:24,076
Honestly, this is totally manageable here.

1276
00:48:24,076 --> 00:48:26,862
Apparently, the line
usually takes like 50 years.

1277
00:48:28,335 --> 00:48:31,081
[Today the line is super short]
This is really okay. Totally okay.

1278
00:48:31,081 --> 00:48:33,470
Oh, so the name changed like this.

1279
00:48:33,470 --> 00:48:36,045
The market is 100 years old,
and the bakery is about 40 or 50.

1280
00:48:36,045 --> 00:48:37,679
We got fooled.

1281
00:48:37,679 --> 00:48:39,751
Huh? It said 1913 though.

1282
00:48:39,751 --> 00:48:42,235
[Here's what happened]

1283
00:48:42,235 --> 00:48:45,482
[Tto*** Bakery is inside
the Songjeong Station Market]

1284
00:48:45,482 --> 00:48:48,318
[Songjeong Station Market was built in 1913
and is 103 years old]

1285
00:48:48,318 --> 00:48:51,121
[Tto*** Bakery went through many names]

1286
00:48:51,121 --> 00:48:53,787
[It started in 1981 and is 45 years old]

1287
00:48:53,787 --> 00:48:55,042
That bread's over 100 years old.

1288
00:48:55,042 --> 00:48:56,867
[Grandpa, you were only half right]

1289
00:48:57,594 --> 00:48:59,729
- The wait isn't as long as I thought.
- Yeah.

1290
00:48:59,729 --> 00:49:02,062
- Yeah, thankfully.
- Because we did the open run.

1291
00:49:02,062 --> 00:49:04,112
[Proud]

1292
00:49:04,112 --> 00:49:07,270
[They grab the tongs and charge in]

1293
00:49:07,270 --> 00:49:10,185
[Starting with the garlic bread]
- Garlic. - Start with that one, yeah.

1294
00:49:11,841 --> 00:49:15,004
[Tightly pursed lips]

1295
00:49:15,004 --> 00:49:17,232
[Woo Shik, pouting his lips,
is so cute to them]

1296
00:49:17,232 --> 00:49:18,982
- And then? Blueberry.
- Blueberry.

1297
00:49:18,982 --> 00:49:20,544
Blueberry?

1298
00:49:20,544 --> 00:49:24,656
[Blueberry bread, come on over]

1299
00:49:24,656 --> 00:49:26,703
- Next is corn bread.
- Corn bread.

1300
00:49:26,703 --> 00:49:28,661
[In it goes]

1301
00:49:28,661 --> 00:49:31,627
[The trio of breads gathered together snugly]

1302
00:49:31,627 --> 00:49:33,007
Then what about you, Yumi?

1303
00:49:33,007 --> 00:49:35,035
I'll get one of those hotteok.

1304
00:49:35,035 --> 00:49:36,669
- This one...
- One.

1305
00:49:36,669 --> 00:49:37,902
Can we get this too?

1306
00:49:37,902 --> 00:49:39,769
- Would you like one?
- Yes.

1307
00:49:39,769 --> 00:49:43,122
- But don't we need milk?
- Oh, let's grab milk.

1308
00:49:43,122 --> 00:49:45,275
They only have strawberry milk.

1309
00:49:45,275 --> 00:49:46,943
Just one. Oh, two.

1310
00:49:46,943 --> 00:49:48,311
But I feel like it'll get dry in our throats.

1311
00:49:48,311 --> 00:49:51,092
- Three.
- Three.

1312
00:49:51,092 --> 00:49:52,506
Strawberry milk does sound good though.

1313
00:49:52,506 --> 00:49:54,384
[Compromise reached one pack per person]

1314
00:49:54,384 --> 00:49:57,099
[Expense report, Tto Bread -18,700 won,
Remaining balance: 281,300 won]

1315
00:49:57,099 --> 00:49:58,710
Thank you!

1316
00:49:59,395 --> 00:50:02,201
[10:26 AM, Departing for Wando Island]

1317
00:50:02,201 --> 00:50:03,960
Man, this bread smell...

1318
00:50:03,960 --> 00:50:05,426
Let's eat one on the way.

1319
00:50:05,426 --> 00:50:07,095
Shall we start with the corn bread first?

1320
00:50:07,095 --> 00:50:09,265
- Corn bread.
- Or shall we start with this one first?

1321
00:50:09,265 --> 00:50:10,385
Corn bread.

1322
00:50:10,385 --> 00:50:11,701
[Corn bread enters the scene]

1323
00:50:11,701 --> 00:50:13,002
[Pre-meal aroma check]

1324
00:50:13,002 --> 00:50:14,408
Wow!

1325
00:50:14,408 --> 00:50:15,569
[Yumi gets a sniff too]

1326
00:50:15,569 --> 00:50:16,887
Oh...

1327
00:50:17,848 --> 00:50:19,007
- Everyone in?
- Yeah.

1328
00:50:19,007 --> 00:50:22,111
[Only after checking even the staff,
their partners in fate]

1329
00:50:22,111 --> 00:50:23,446
Here we go.

1330
00:50:23,446 --> 00:50:26,628
[Heading to Wando, the southernmost village]
- Let's go! - Let's go!

1331
00:50:26,628 --> 00:50:29,981
[About a two-hour drive by car]

1332
00:50:29,981 --> 00:50:32,121
Still, I didn't expect we'd buy them this fast.

1333
00:50:32,121 --> 00:50:33,869
It's because we saw that poop truck earlier.

1334
00:50:33,869 --> 00:50:36,759
Yeah, maybe that's it.
Maybe it really was because of the poop truck.

1335
00:50:36,759 --> 00:50:38,769
[You could call it the luck brought
by the poop truck...]

1336
00:50:41,436 --> 00:50:43,500
[Tearing off a huge chunk]

1337
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:45,689
[Making sure driver Seo Jun gets some first]

1338
00:50:45,689 --> 00:50:47,732
[Big-mouth Seo Jun]

1339
00:50:48,705 --> 00:50:50,059
Wow.

1340
00:50:50,059 --> 00:50:52,004
This is seriously delicious.

1341
00:50:55,159 --> 00:50:58,058
[Only after taking care of Seo Jun and Yumi,
he takes a big bite]

1342
00:50:58,058 --> 00:51:00,153
[Three consecutive exclamations]

1343
00:51:00,153 --> 00:51:02,421
[The fresh bread keeps bringing out reactions]
Wow, this is really good.

1344
00:51:02,421 --> 00:51:06,155
Wow. It's my first time eating bread
like this right after it came out.

1345
00:51:06,155 --> 00:51:08,563
Me too. I think it tastes even better
because it's freshly made.

1346
00:51:08,563 --> 00:51:11,703
Yeah. This is really good though.

1347
00:51:11,703 --> 00:51:13,902
[Even when it's delicious, still tiny bites]

1348
00:51:13,902 --> 00:51:15,426
The bread is just melting.

1349
00:51:15,426 --> 00:51:17,680
[Even melting bread
can't make the bites bigger]

1350
00:51:18,601 --> 00:51:22,582
So, that old man yesterday
waited through that whole line and all?

1351
00:51:22,582 --> 00:51:24,206
- Exactly.
- He bought it like that...

1352
00:51:24,206 --> 00:51:25,675
[Thanks to you, we enjoyed the bread, sir]

1353
00:51:25,675 --> 00:51:27,970
- Can you pass me some milk?
- Yeah.

1354
00:51:27,970 --> 00:51:29,805
Doesn't your stomach hurt
when you drink milk in the morning?

1355
00:51:29,805 --> 00:51:30,947
Nope.

1356
00:51:30,947 --> 00:51:33,783
You're blessed. Be thankful to your mother.

1357
00:51:33,783 --> 00:51:35,663
Thank you.

1358
00:51:36,883 --> 00:51:39,429
I think the weather's nice.

1359
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:42,151
The weather today is honestly
unbelievably good.

1360
00:51:42,151 --> 00:51:44,894
I hope the weather in Jeju is nice too.

1361
00:51:44,894 --> 00:51:47,130
Oh, we didn't check the weather in Jeju.

1362
00:51:47,130 --> 00:51:48,669
[These people do not have phones]

1363
00:51:48,669 --> 00:51:50,326
Man, this car is really nice.

1364
00:51:50,326 --> 00:51:52,468
Wow, this is really nice.

1365
00:51:52,468 --> 00:51:54,714
Now, it finally feels like we're traveling.

1366
00:51:54,714 --> 00:51:57,079
I thought this was gonna be an easy trip.

1367
00:51:57,079 --> 00:51:58,875
[Finally feels like a trip after five days]
Me too.

1368
00:51:58,875 --> 00:52:01,895
- But they gave us no information at all.
- Yeah.

1369
00:52:01,895 --> 00:52:03,479
I seriously thought we were going farming.

1370
00:52:03,479 --> 00:52:05,582
Honestly, I thought we were
just filming "Winter Vacation."

1371
00:52:05,582 --> 00:52:08,010
[Accuracy rate: 0%]

1372
00:52:08,010 --> 00:52:09,877
But tomorrow's already the last day.

1373
00:52:09,877 --> 00:52:11,008
Already?

1374
00:52:11,008 --> 00:52:12,716
That's a shame.

1375
00:52:12,716 --> 00:52:14,801
Why does every day feel so long?

1376
00:52:14,801 --> 00:52:16,817
It really does.

1377
00:52:16,817 --> 00:52:18,494
The days are so long.

1378
00:52:18,494 --> 00:52:21,798
It kind of feels like going
to school every day.

1379
00:52:21,798 --> 00:52:24,300
[Wake up, it's time for school]
Waking up in the morning and all.

1380
00:52:24,300 --> 00:52:26,005
We've really come all the way to the end now.

1381
00:52:26,005 --> 00:52:27,215
[One hour before arriving
at the southernmost point]

1382
00:52:27,215 --> 00:52:30,139
Wando Island is basically
the end of the peninsula.

1383
00:52:30,139 --> 00:52:31,941
It's my first time coming this far south.

1384
00:52:31,941 --> 00:52:34,277
The southern tip of Jeollanam-do Province.

1385
00:52:34,277 --> 00:52:36,779
Once we cross the bridge
at the end of Haenam, it's Wando Island.

1386
00:52:36,779 --> 00:52:38,327
[Travel route]

1387
00:52:38,327 --> 00:52:40,763
Our route is seriously insane.

1388
00:52:42,055 --> 00:52:44,659
Ugh, I shouldn't have drunk
that strawberry milk.

1389
00:52:45,254 --> 00:52:47,003
- You drank it?
- Yeah.

1390
00:52:47,003 --> 00:52:48,970
- Want me to pull over?
- No, not yet.

1391
00:52:48,970 --> 00:52:50,927
You said you wouldn't drink it.

1392
00:52:50,927 --> 00:52:54,200
[His expression stiffens instantly...]

1393
00:52:54,200 --> 00:52:57,041
I really shouldn't have drunk
the strawberry milk.

1394
00:52:57,834 --> 00:52:59,135
Did you finish the whole thing?

1395
00:52:59,135 --> 00:53:00,937
No, maybe half?

1396
00:53:00,937 --> 00:53:02,731
Wait, is there no rest stop around here?

1397
00:53:02,731 --> 00:53:04,607
This is a national highway here.

1398
00:53:04,607 --> 00:53:05,815
Seriously, what do we do?

1399
00:53:05,815 --> 00:53:08,168
Because it's exactly 11:30 right now.

1400
00:53:08,168 --> 00:53:09,774
Actually, I should've gone
to the bathroom four minutes ago.

1401
00:53:09,774 --> 00:53:11,826
[11:34 AM, 4 minutes past routine time]
Yeah, it already passed.

1402
00:53:11,826 --> 00:53:14,651
We just have to drive straight
for 42 kilometers.

1403
00:53:14,651 --> 00:53:17,320
42 kilometers? No way.

1404
00:53:17,320 --> 00:53:19,255
I don't see any gas stations.

1405
00:53:19,255 --> 00:53:20,685
This is bad.

1406
00:53:20,685 --> 00:53:24,160
[All I see are mountains and clouds]
I don't see any gas stations around here.

1407
00:53:24,160 --> 00:53:26,396
There's not even a rest stop.

1408
00:53:27,579 --> 00:53:28,596
Take the exit.

1409
00:53:28,596 --> 00:53:30,083
[Wait... this is bad...]

1410
00:53:30,083 --> 00:53:31,442
Yumi, do you have tissues?

1411
00:53:31,442 --> 00:53:33,302
[Preparing for the worst-case scenario]
Yeah, I do.

1412
00:53:33,302 --> 00:53:35,400
They said pressing somewhere
on your hand helps.

1413
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:36,772
Oh, right.

1414
00:53:36,772 --> 00:53:39,275
- They said it goes away.
- I learned that before.

1415
00:53:39,275 --> 00:53:41,711
[Even turning to traditional medicine...]
It's a poop emergency.

1416
00:53:41,711 --> 00:53:43,646
Yeah, they said it settles down
if you press there.

1417
00:53:43,646 --> 00:53:45,548
It goes down? Shouldn't it go up instead?

1418
00:53:45,548 --> 00:53:48,054
[Genius...]

1419
00:53:48,054 --> 00:53:50,508
[At that moment,
a stone tower appears on the right...]

1420
00:53:51,299 --> 00:53:53,080
What is that?

1421
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:54,699
- No.
- Oh, guess not.

1422
00:53:54,699 --> 00:53:56,893
- Go, go!
- Wait.

1423
00:53:56,893 --> 00:53:59,295
- You've gotta go!
- Where are you going?

1424
00:53:59,295 --> 00:54:01,408
[The place Woo Shik
absentmindedly passed by was...]

1425
00:54:01,408 --> 00:54:04,333
[Public bathroom]

1426
00:54:04,333 --> 00:54:06,878
- Oh, a bathroom.
- It's a bathroom.

1427
00:54:06,878 --> 00:54:09,005
Woo Shik said it wasn't the bathroom.

1428
00:54:09,005 --> 00:54:11,207
[Speechless]
Woo Shik...

1429
00:54:11,207 --> 00:54:13,198
Hey, you said you needed to go!

1430
00:54:13,198 --> 00:54:14,628
Woo Shik said it wasn't the bathroom.

1431
00:54:14,628 --> 00:54:16,879
- No, I didn't see that.
- I was seriously about to go there earlier.

1432
00:54:16,879 --> 00:54:18,955
- I seriously didn't see it.
- I was seriously about to go there earlier.

1433
00:54:18,955 --> 00:54:20,569
How could you not see it?

1434
00:54:20,569 --> 00:54:22,206
Why didn't you go in there earlier?

1435
00:54:22,206 --> 00:54:25,127
You said it wasn't a bathroom.

1436
00:54:25,127 --> 00:54:26,593
- Woo Shik, are you okay?
- Yeah.

1437
00:54:26,593 --> 00:54:28,557
I don't think there'll be another one.

1438
00:54:28,557 --> 00:54:29,668
What do I do?

1439
00:54:29,668 --> 00:54:31,628
What are we gonna do about Woo Shik?

1440
00:54:31,628 --> 00:54:33,478
At this rate, we're just gonna arrive.

1441
00:54:33,478 --> 00:54:35,971
At this rate, we're actually
gonna make it there.

1442
00:54:35,971 --> 00:54:38,668
Thanks to you, the ETA keeps getting earlier.

1443
00:54:38,668 --> 00:54:40,147
[20 minutes before arrival]

1444
00:54:40,147 --> 00:54:41,938
But why is literally nothing showing up?

1445
00:54:41,938 --> 00:54:45,864
There's seriously nothing.
That one earlier must've been our last chance.

1446
00:54:45,864 --> 00:54:50,383
[Even after driving for a long time,
no bathroom appears...]

1447
00:54:50,383 --> 00:54:52,815
Wow, there really isn't one
all the way to the end.

1448
00:54:52,815 --> 00:54:54,751
Ah, what do I do?

1449
00:54:55,430 --> 00:54:58,054
We're seriously just gonna arrive like this.

1450
00:54:58,054 --> 00:55:00,823
We got three minutes closer now.

1451
00:55:00,823 --> 00:55:02,208
[12 minutes before arrival]

1452
00:55:02,208 --> 00:55:04,193
I can't even lean back right now.

1453
00:55:04,193 --> 00:55:06,863
- Why?
- I'm on a mission to get him to a bathroom.

1454
00:55:06,863 --> 00:55:08,656
What do we do about Woo Shik?

1455
00:55:08,656 --> 00:55:09,928
Hold it in.

1456
00:55:09,928 --> 00:55:11,608
- Woo Shik's in a bathroom emergency!
- A man is dying here.

1457
00:55:11,608 --> 00:55:12,969
I'm dying!

1458
00:55:12,969 --> 00:55:14,689
[United as one]

1459
00:55:14,689 --> 00:55:17,755
[Finally, on the bridge to Wando Island]
He needs to use the bathroom!

1460
00:55:17,755 --> 00:55:19,942
- Ah, but we're basically here now.
- We're basically here.

1461
00:55:19,942 --> 00:55:21,410
You'll be okay now, Woo Shik.

1462
00:55:21,410 --> 00:55:23,453
Oh, thank goodness.

1463
00:55:23,453 --> 00:55:24,683
It's the ocean.

1464
00:55:24,683 --> 00:55:26,649
[Right as they enter Wando Island, they see...]
We're in Wando Island now.

1465
00:55:26,649 --> 00:55:28,028
Oh, Wando Island.

1466
00:55:28,028 --> 00:55:29,843
Wow, it's Wando Island!

1467
00:55:29,843 --> 00:55:31,814
[Where the southernmost sea and islands meet]

1468
00:55:32,574 --> 00:55:37,026
[This place is lined with ships
waiting to depart]

1469
00:55:37,026 --> 00:55:39,328
[This is Wando Port]

1470
00:55:39,328 --> 00:55:41,942
[Wando Ferry Terminal]

1471
00:55:41,942 --> 00:55:43,099
Wow, this is amazing.

1472
00:55:43,099 --> 00:55:45,701
[A refreshing sense of awe naturally escapes]

1473
00:55:45,701 --> 00:55:49,178
We really came all the way
to the end of the map.

1474
00:55:49,178 --> 00:55:51,204
This is really the end right here.

1475
00:55:51,204 --> 00:55:52,475
[They finally made it
to the map's southern edge]

1476
00:55:52,475 --> 00:55:56,312
- Wow, this place is beautiful.
- I think that's the passenger terminal.

1477
00:55:56,312 --> 00:55:58,795
I think that's the one we're taking.

1478
00:55:58,795 --> 00:56:01,684
[A heavy presence felt even from afar...]
- This is so pretty. - Isn't it that big one?

1479
00:56:01,684 --> 00:56:03,862
Yeah, it says "Sil*** Cloud."

1480
00:56:03,862 --> 00:56:05,515
Just go into the terminal.

1481
00:56:05,515 --> 00:56:08,589
- And go to the bathroom first.
- Yeah, the terminal entrance.

1482
00:56:08,589 --> 00:56:11,160
[First, take care of urgent business...]
It's okay for now.

1483
00:56:11,160 --> 00:56:12,598
He's just gonna use the bathroom real quick.

1484
00:56:12,598 --> 00:56:14,795
Yeah, just hurry up.

1485
00:56:14,795 --> 00:56:16,833
[Relieved]

1486
00:56:16,833 --> 00:56:18,868
- There's only ten minutes left?
- It opened.

1487
00:56:18,868 --> 00:56:21,044
[1:50 PM, Wando Ferry Terminal]

1488
00:56:21,044 --> 00:56:22,318
Oh, ID.

1489
00:56:22,318 --> 00:56:24,175
- Oh, ID.
- Did you take your ID out?

1490
00:56:24,175 --> 00:56:25,835
Yeah, I did.

1491
00:56:25,835 --> 00:56:27,732
Three people going to Jeju...

1492
00:56:27,732 --> 00:56:29,412
- 3 o'clock.
- 3 o'clock!

1493
00:56:29,412 --> 00:56:31,132
- Didn't you make a reservation separately?
- Yes.

1494
00:56:31,132 --> 00:56:32,815
Would you like the standard cabin?

1495
00:56:32,815 --> 00:56:34,984
Yes, the cheapest one.

1496
00:56:34,984 --> 00:56:38,230
The standard third-class cabin is 35,600 won.

1497
00:56:38,230 --> 00:56:40,159
- Wasn't it 32,000 won?
- 33,000 won...

1498
00:56:40,159 --> 00:56:41,838
With the fuel surcharge

1499
00:56:41,838 --> 00:56:44,889
and terminal fee of 2,800 won
added to the 32,000 won...

1500
00:56:44,889 --> 00:56:47,366
[Instant acceptance]
- Ah, okay. - Yeah.

1501
00:56:47,366 --> 00:56:49,432
Oh, I forgot about that fee.

1502
00:56:49,432 --> 00:56:53,135
For three people,
the total will be 106,800 won.

1503
00:56:53,135 --> 00:56:55,662
[Remaining balance: 138,900 won]
Go to the regular entrance on the other side...

1504
00:56:55,662 --> 00:56:57,184
Yeah.

1505
00:56:57,184 --> 00:56:59,008
There's not much left, right?

1506
00:56:59,008 --> 00:57:00,309
What are we gonna do about lodging?

1507
00:57:00,309 --> 00:57:01,779
[Already running low on money...]

1508
00:57:01,779 --> 00:57:03,288
Should we have a quick meeting?

1509
00:57:03,288 --> 00:57:04,729
- Should we talk here for a sec?
- Yeah.

1510
00:57:04,729 --> 00:57:06,725
[Actually, the Jeju strategy meeting
had already started at the restaurant...]

1511
00:57:06,725 --> 00:57:07,750
[One hour earlier, restaurant near the harbor]

1512
00:57:07,750 --> 00:57:10,753
There's this black pork place that
the security guy told me about.

1513
00:57:10,753 --> 00:57:13,589
And it's just sitting alone by the beach.

1514
00:57:13,589 --> 00:57:16,197
So whenever I went to Jeju,
I always went there.

1515
00:57:16,197 --> 00:57:19,240
Honestly, I want to try that cutlassfish place.

1516
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:21,930
- But you don't know the name, right?
- I can just call Sang Bae.

1517
00:57:21,930 --> 00:57:24,618
[So they decided where to go...]
- Okay, then let's go with that. - Yeah.

1518
00:57:24,618 --> 00:57:25,805
How much do we have left?

1519
00:57:25,805 --> 00:57:28,354
[The problem is... they don't have much money]

1520
00:57:28,354 --> 00:57:31,023
138,900 won.

1521
00:57:31,023 --> 00:57:32,160
That's tight, huh?

1522
00:57:32,160 --> 00:57:36,190
- But the meat is expensive too.
- Feels like we might not even get to eat meat.

1523
00:57:36,190 --> 00:57:40,681
But our original goal for going to Jeju
was to eat good food.

1524
00:57:40,681 --> 00:57:43,360
[It's not going easy on them
until the very end...]

1525
00:57:44,025 --> 00:57:45,375
What time do we arrive?

1526
00:57:45,375 --> 00:57:46,600
5:40.

1527
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:50,558
So for the pork place,
you'll call someone you know first.

1528
00:57:50,558 --> 00:57:51,635
Yes.

1529
00:57:51,635 --> 00:57:53,464
And for the grilled fish...

1530
00:57:53,464 --> 00:57:54,905
If he doesn't answer.

1531
00:57:54,905 --> 00:57:58,559
But if we have time tomorrow,
we'll eat that for breakfast.

1532
00:57:58,559 --> 00:58:00,594
Would they open in the morning though?

1533
00:58:00,594 --> 00:58:03,238
It'd be nice for breakfast, but...

1534
00:58:03,238 --> 00:58:05,173
- The return flight though...
- Oh, yes.

1535
00:58:05,173 --> 00:58:07,841
- We checked that out.
- Yeah.

1536
00:58:07,841 --> 00:58:10,611
- You checked it first when you three searched.
- Yeah.

1537
00:58:10,611 --> 00:58:13,580
- The early morning flight back on March 1st.
- Yeah.

1538
00:58:13,580 --> 00:58:15,315
- It's 110,000 won?
- 110,000...

1539
00:58:15,315 --> 00:58:16,830
Why is this so expensive?

1540
00:58:16,830 --> 00:58:18,558
Scroll down, scroll down.

1541
00:58:18,558 --> 00:58:21,215
- Was it... 110,000 won per person?
- 110,000 won.

1542
00:58:21,215 --> 00:58:24,578
Just in case, we reserved a few seats.

1543
00:58:24,578 --> 00:58:26,193
- You reserved them?
- The 110,000 won ones?

1544
00:58:26,193 --> 00:58:29,290
Yeah, we reserved them.
So three tickets total 330,000 won.

1545
00:58:29,290 --> 00:58:33,805
So for the last day, we can substitute that
with the plane tickets.

1546
00:58:33,805 --> 00:58:37,250
You probably have to go straight
from Gimpo to a livestream, right?

1547
00:58:37,250 --> 00:58:40,613
So you should save a few thousand won
for subway fare today...

1548
00:58:40,613 --> 00:58:43,149
[Hahahahaha]
Then wait, there's that though...

1549
00:58:43,149 --> 00:58:45,253
- Do we draw again tomorrow morning?
- Yeah, you do.

1550
00:58:45,253 --> 00:58:47,106
You'll draw benefits on the last day too.

1551
00:58:47,106 --> 00:58:50,009
If you get the car, getting to the company
from Gimpo will be easy.

1552
00:58:50,009 --> 00:58:52,091
- And if you draw the phone,
- Yeah, that's right.

1553
00:58:52,091 --> 00:58:53,541
you'll get it immediately.

1554
00:58:53,541 --> 00:58:55,957
But shouldn't you just give it to us tomorrow?

1555
00:58:55,957 --> 00:58:58,493
- We'll give it to you after the livestream.
- After the livestream?

1556
00:58:58,493 --> 00:59:01,463
So tomorrow, it's either
the phone or the car. Right?

1557
00:59:01,463 --> 00:59:02,868
- The car is definitely the best.
- Yeah.

1558
00:59:02,868 --> 00:59:06,026
Since tomorrow technically isn't a day
you need lodging...

1559
00:59:06,026 --> 00:59:08,963
we'll replace lodging with
something appropriate.

1560
00:59:08,963 --> 00:59:11,110
Yes, thank you.

1561
00:59:11,110 --> 00:59:13,866
[But more importantly...]

1562
00:59:13,866 --> 00:59:15,223
[Q. What time is the departure to Gimpo?]
What time is it?

1563
00:59:15,223 --> 00:59:17,939
[A. 7:10 AM]
Departure is at 7:10 in the morning.

1564
00:59:17,939 --> 00:59:19,956
7:10 in the morning?

1565
00:59:19,956 --> 00:59:23,125
So after we arrive, we only get 12 hours
before leaving again?

1566
00:59:23,125 --> 00:59:26,717
[12-hour Jeju trip]
It'll be exactly a 12-hour trip.

1567
00:59:26,717 --> 00:59:30,126
Guess we'll at least get to see
a nice Jeju night.

1568
00:59:30,126 --> 00:59:32,186
Wait, we arrive at night, right?

1569
00:59:32,186 --> 00:59:33,392
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1570
00:59:33,392 --> 00:59:34,730
Oh, then...

1571
00:59:34,730 --> 00:59:35,882
Ah...

1572
00:59:35,882 --> 00:59:38,439
- So we leave in the morning?
- Yeah.

1573
00:59:38,439 --> 00:59:41,114
It's not even morning.
If we have to wake up and go to the airport...

1574
00:59:41,114 --> 00:59:43,979
- A 7:10 flight?
- Departure is at 7:10 AM.

1575
00:59:43,979 --> 00:59:48,077
If that's departure time,
we definitely need to be there by 6:30 AM.

1576
00:59:48,077 --> 00:59:49,388
Well...

1577
00:59:49,388 --> 00:59:50,879
then,

1578
00:59:50,879 --> 00:59:54,854
that wouldn't be the Jeju trip I was picturing?

1579
00:59:54,854 --> 00:59:55,952
[Even below expectations...]

1580
00:59:55,952 --> 00:59:57,504
What time is sunrise?

1581
00:59:57,504 --> 00:59:59,489
Can you at least tell us what time sunrise is?

1582
00:59:59,489 --> 01:00:01,018
So we can at least see if it's possible.

1583
01:00:01,018 --> 01:00:04,680
Tomorrow's sunrise is at 7:03 AM.

1584
01:00:04,680 --> 01:00:07,633
- Wow, then we won't even get to see the sun.
- Right, it's still winter.

1585
01:00:07,633 --> 01:00:09,335
Guess we'll see it from the plane.

1586
01:00:09,335 --> 01:00:12,029
So it'll just end with us
looking at darkness the whole time?

1587
01:00:12,029 --> 01:00:14,464
[Jeju Island: Night Mode...]
The sun will rise as the plane takes off.

1588
01:00:14,464 --> 01:00:16,444
Oh, then we'll at least see the sunset.

1589
01:00:16,444 --> 01:00:19,392
- Nice.
- We arrive at sunset and leave at sunrise.

1590
01:00:19,392 --> 01:00:20,975
[Laughing]

1591
01:00:20,975 --> 01:00:22,485
You're right.

1592
01:00:23,116 --> 01:00:25,961
Wow, but this is my first time
traveling to Jeju like this.

1593
01:00:25,961 --> 01:00:28,083
- Me too.
- This is gonna get fun.

1594
01:00:28,083 --> 01:00:30,817
- Woo Shik, you like tough stuff anyway.
- Yeah.

1595
01:00:30,817 --> 01:00:33,253
12 hours in Jeju... wow.

1596
01:00:33,253 --> 01:00:34,861
We should board at 2:30 PM

1597
01:00:34,861 --> 01:00:36,986
- for the 3:00 PM departure.
- What time is it now?

1598
01:00:36,986 --> 01:00:39,653
- Oh right, you guys don't know the time.
- Yeah.

1599
01:00:39,653 --> 01:00:44,391
[Wando Ferry Terminal]
[2:45 PM, Boarding the ferry]

1600
01:00:44,391 --> 01:00:48,608
[Before they knew it,
3 PM boarding was approaching...]

1601
01:00:48,608 --> 01:00:49,999
- Are there two of you?
- Yeah.

1602
01:00:49,999 --> 01:00:51,478
[First, ticket check before entering the gate!]

1603
01:00:51,478 --> 01:00:54,672
Yes, once you go up there,
they'll check your tickets and IDs.

1604
01:00:55,277 --> 01:00:57,551
[And so everyone heads through the gate...]

1605
01:00:57,551 --> 01:01:00,419
He stepped in poop!

1606
01:01:00,419 --> 01:01:02,375
- What is this?
- Dog poop!

1607
01:01:02,375 --> 01:01:04,291
- Who stepped on it?
- Seriously?

1608
01:01:04,291 --> 01:01:06,361
[So here's what happened...]
Who was it?

1609
01:01:07,197 --> 01:01:10,340
[There was dog poop near the boarding gate...]

1610
01:01:10,340 --> 01:01:13,430
[The camera director almost
stepped on it while rushing...]

1611
01:01:13,430 --> 01:01:18,004
- But we saw a poop truck this morning too.
- Poop truck, then dog poop... this is insane.

1612
01:01:18,004 --> 01:01:21,047
[Will two poop sightings a day bring luck?]

1613
01:01:21,047 --> 01:01:24,213
- Wow, it's huge!
- It's seriously huge.

1614
01:01:24,931 --> 01:01:27,225
The parking lot feels like a giant supermarket.

1615
01:01:27,225 --> 01:01:29,770
[An overwhelming scale
you can't take in at once]

1616
01:01:29,770 --> 01:01:31,859
[After the final ticket and ID check]

1617
01:01:31,859 --> 01:01:33,485
Thank you!

1618
01:01:33,485 --> 01:01:37,034
[They finally begin boarding the ship]

1619
01:01:37,034 --> 01:01:38,844
Wow!

1620
01:01:38,844 --> 01:01:41,222
[So cool and fascinating]

1621
01:01:41,222 --> 01:01:43,246
Wow, it's enormous!

1622
01:01:44,256 --> 01:01:46,326
Wow, we're actually riding this.

1623
01:01:46,326 --> 01:01:49,140
[Once inside, the trip to Jeju
finally feels real]

1624
01:01:49,140 --> 01:01:51,398
[Go, go]

1625
01:01:51,398 --> 01:01:53,376
- Please move this way.
- Yes.

1626
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:55,605
Oh? There's even a convenience store.

1627
01:01:55,605 --> 01:01:56,816
- What is it?
- Duty-free.

1628
01:01:56,816 --> 01:01:59,428
Oh, so there's duty-free shopping.

1629
01:01:59,428 --> 01:02:01,635
Oh, nice! Oh, you can see outside.

1630
01:02:01,635 --> 01:02:04,308
Oh wow, it's fast!

1631
01:02:04,308 --> 01:02:06,241
Director, look at the ocean.

1632
01:02:07,170 --> 01:02:09,288
[Director Choi heads over]
It's outside here.

1633
01:02:09,288 --> 01:02:10,512
The ocean.

1634
01:02:10,512 --> 01:02:13,108
Look, look. It's super fast.

1635
01:02:15,791 --> 01:02:18,531
[White foam crashing at the tips of the waves]

1636
01:02:23,303 --> 01:02:25,784
2 hours and 40 minutes for us?

1637
01:02:25,784 --> 01:02:27,339
Should we sleep for an hour?

1638
01:02:27,339 --> 01:02:28,975
I'm gonna eat some bread.

1639
01:02:28,975 --> 01:02:30,594
I want the blueberry one.

1640
01:02:30,594 --> 01:02:33,125
[First, they fill up on leftover bread...]
I'll have hotteok.

1641
01:02:33,125 --> 01:02:36,269
Blueberry smoothie. Let me have a bite.

1642
01:02:36,269 --> 01:02:38,626
[Can't resist, takes a big bite
of blueberry bread]

1643
01:02:40,592 --> 01:02:42,524
This is good too.

1644
01:02:43,263 --> 01:02:44,578
The jam...

1645
01:02:44,578 --> 01:02:46,893
- they added it in.
- You like it, don't you?

1646
01:02:46,893 --> 01:02:49,172
[Well, he's a naturally fun guy after all]

1647
01:02:53,696 --> 01:02:55,108
[Sounds of savoring coming from everywhere...]

1648
01:02:55,108 --> 01:02:57,736
- What's that?
- Mugwort rice-cake hotteok.

1649
01:02:57,736 --> 01:02:59,295
[Trying it after seeing Yumi eat it...]

1650
01:02:59,295 --> 01:03:00,957
Oh?

1651
01:03:00,957 --> 01:03:02,700
This is it, this is the one.

1652
01:03:02,700 --> 01:03:05,086
It kind of tastes like rice cake. Rice cake.

1653
01:03:05,742 --> 01:03:06,825
It's good.

1654
01:03:06,825 --> 01:03:08,436
[Even the youngest switches
from blueberry to mugwort...]

1655
01:03:08,436 --> 01:03:09,499
Whoa!

1656
01:03:09,499 --> 01:03:12,163
[So good it knocks you out]

1657
01:03:12,163 --> 01:03:14,848
- Number one.
- Corn bread is number one, but for me...

1658
01:03:14,848 --> 01:03:16,556
This is number one for me.

1659
01:03:16,556 --> 01:03:17,650
[Straight into my mouth]

1660
01:03:17,650 --> 01:03:18,788
It's delicious.

1661
01:03:18,788 --> 01:03:20,393
- Try this once.
- Just have a taste.

1662
01:03:20,393 --> 01:03:23,007
[A destiny-bound group that
even shares a single slice of bread...]

1663
01:03:23,007 --> 01:03:25,013
- It's seriously good.
- Right?

1664
01:03:25,013 --> 01:03:27,523
Right? It's like rice cake, right?

1665
01:03:27,523 --> 01:03:29,726
How's the budget situation
looking for this Jeju trip?

1666
01:03:29,726 --> 01:03:32,636
We're tight on money right now...

1667
01:03:32,636 --> 01:03:36,007
Because we don't even know
how much the lodging costs, right?

1668
01:03:36,007 --> 01:03:37,004
Right.

1669
01:03:37,004 --> 01:03:39,236
[Without phones, there's no way
to check lodging prices...]

1670
01:03:39,236 --> 01:03:40,962
Where the black pork place is...

1671
01:03:40,962 --> 01:03:43,337
- that's the most important thing.
- Right.

1672
01:03:43,337 --> 01:03:46,319
Huh? Can we use the phone chance here?

1673
01:03:46,319 --> 01:03:48,731
- Do we even have a signal?
- But does it work?

1674
01:03:48,731 --> 01:03:51,123
The signal's actually really good right now.

1675
01:03:51,123 --> 01:03:52,892
- Should we try?
- Try it?

1676
01:03:52,892 --> 01:03:54,719
Yeah, wait... what should I say?

1677
01:03:54,719 --> 01:03:57,208
- So keep it short.
- Yeah.

1678
01:03:57,208 --> 01:03:59,596
I'll ask you directly.

1679
01:03:59,596 --> 01:04:01,171
We're heading to Jeju right now,

1680
01:04:01,171 --> 01:04:04,003
- so could you tell us that black pork place?
- Shorten it more, more...

1681
01:04:04,003 --> 01:04:07,241
What was the name of that
Jeju black pork place again?

1682
01:04:07,241 --> 01:04:10,765
Where? Which black pork place?

1683
01:04:10,765 --> 01:04:13,055
- That sounds like I'm on the phone with you.
- Oh, right...

1684
01:04:13,055 --> 01:04:14,787
[Suddenly back to his real self]

1685
01:04:14,787 --> 01:04:16,304
But if I say it, he'll know right away.

1686
01:04:16,304 --> 01:04:17,431
- Really?
- Yeah.

1687
01:04:17,431 --> 01:04:18,941
- Then let's do it.
- Okay, let's go with that.

1688
01:04:18,941 --> 01:04:20,679
- Okay.
- Right now?

1689
01:04:20,679 --> 01:04:22,946
- Yeah.
- Hey, is there anything to write on?

1690
01:04:22,946 --> 01:04:24,646
Did you bring a notebook or something?

1691
01:04:24,646 --> 01:04:25,924
Oh, that's over there.

1692
01:04:25,924 --> 01:04:27,622
[Unfortunately, it's in the car...]

1693
01:04:27,622 --> 01:04:29,845
- If you need something to write on.
- Oh, yes.

1694
01:04:29,845 --> 01:04:32,298
[Notebook provided as humanitarian aid]
Just in case he gives us the address.

1695
01:04:32,298 --> 01:04:34,146
[Emergency note-taking mode]

1696
01:04:34,146 --> 01:04:35,582
"I'm filming right now.

1697
01:04:35,582 --> 01:04:38,795
Where's that Jeju black pork place?"

1698
01:04:38,795 --> 01:04:40,572
"The one we went to before."

1699
01:04:41,413 --> 01:04:43,342
- "I'm filming right now..."
- Yeah.

1700
01:04:43,342 --> 01:04:45,340
"Jeju black pork place."

1701
01:04:45,340 --> 01:04:47,780
"Jeju black pork place."

1702
01:04:47,780 --> 01:04:49,916
"Name, location."

1703
01:04:49,916 --> 01:04:52,961
[Feels like it's 100 days before the CSAT...]
"Name, location..."

1704
01:04:52,961 --> 01:04:54,994
- I don't think we'll get the address.
- As long as we know the area...

1705
01:04:54,994 --> 01:04:57,596
We just need to know which side is on.

1706
01:04:57,596 --> 01:04:58,828
- Location.
- Location.

1707
01:04:58,828 --> 01:05:00,340
- That's all we need to know.
- Yeah.

1708
01:05:00,340 --> 01:05:01,944
[Key points: filming, ask for the
Jeju black pork place name, get the location]

1709
01:05:01,944 --> 01:05:03,152
That's it.

1710
01:05:03,152 --> 01:05:04,668
[All set and fully prepared...]

1711
01:05:04,668 --> 01:05:07,533
- Let's go.
- From the moment you touch your phone...

1712
01:05:07,533 --> 01:05:09,743
- No, it starts the moment he clicks it.
- Clicking it?

1713
01:05:09,743 --> 01:05:12,518
Counting from touching it is too harsh...

1714
01:05:12,518 --> 01:05:15,218
- From when the lock screen opens.
- At least I have to turn it on.

1715
01:05:15,218 --> 01:05:17,734
It's already on. I turned it on just now.

1716
01:05:17,734 --> 01:05:20,222
Then just set it down here.

1717
01:05:20,898 --> 01:05:24,366
[Including Seo Jun's phone,
Yumi &amp; Woo Shik's phones are ready too]

1718
01:05:24,366 --> 01:05:27,720
[Even more nervous after trying it]
Ugh, please pick up right away.

1719
01:05:27,720 --> 01:05:29,777
- Please say "start."
- Okay.

1720
01:05:29,777 --> 01:05:32,595
["Start" triggers a 1:30 countdown]

1721
01:05:32,595 --> 01:05:34,494
My hands are sweating.

1722
01:05:34,494 --> 01:05:37,063
What are you gonna do after turning it on?
Where are you going first?

1723
01:05:37,063 --> 01:05:38,939
- Phone.
- Phone.

1724
01:05:38,939 --> 01:05:40,966
- Shin Won Gi.
- Shin Won Gi.

1725
01:05:40,966 --> 01:05:42,776
[1. Phone, 2. Shin Won Gi, 3. Call]
- Call. - Call.

1726
01:05:42,776 --> 01:05:44,481
Won Gi, I'm filming in Jeju right now...

1727
01:05:44,481 --> 01:05:47,886
- Name and location of that black pork place?
- Quickly.

1728
01:05:47,886 --> 01:05:49,025
Okay.

1729
01:05:49,999 --> 01:05:52,111
- Start!
- Start!

1730
01:05:52,111 --> 01:05:54,313
[1 minute 30 second timer ON]

1731
01:05:54,313 --> 01:05:55,715
[He quickly opened the contacts, but...]

1732
01:05:55,715 --> 01:05:56,975
Hey, hey!

1733
01:05:56,975 --> 01:05:59,352
[He accidentally tapped the wrong contact...]
Hey, hey, hey!

1734
01:05:59,352 --> 01:06:01,723
- Ten seconds have passed.
- Huh? What?

1735
01:06:01,723 --> 01:06:02,808
Hey, why isn't it there?

1736
01:06:02,808 --> 01:06:03,953
[Finally found Won Gi]

1737
01:06:03,953 --> 01:06:05,283
[Calling immediately]

1738
01:06:05,283 --> 01:06:06,335
[Outgoing call begins]

1739
01:06:06,335 --> 01:06:07,560
He made the call in ten seconds.

1740
01:06:07,560 --> 01:06:09,958
[Mistakes, ten seconds is a good start]

1741
01:06:09,958 --> 01:06:11,015
Turn up the volume.

1742
01:06:11,015 --> 01:06:12,897
[Will he pick up?]

1743
01:06:12,897 --> 01:06:14,466
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Won Gi, Won Gi!

1744
01:06:14,466 --> 01:06:17,765
[Call connected successfully]
Won Gi, I'm filming right now.

1745
01:06:17,765 --> 01:06:20,766
<i>- Oh, yeah.</i>
- You know that black pork place in Jeju?

1746
01:06:20,766 --> 01:06:23,915
<i>- Oh, yeah.</i>
- Name and location of that black pork place?

1747
01:06:23,915 --> 01:06:26,245
[They're in a hurry]
I can't receive texts right now,

1748
01:06:26,245 --> 01:06:27,736
- just tell me.
- Out loud.

1749
01:06:27,736 --> 01:06:29,938
<i>I won't say it right now. I'll send it to you.</i>

1750
01:06:29,938 --> 01:06:32,226
No, no... just say it.

1751
01:06:32,226 --> 01:06:34,820
- The name, the restaurant name.
<i>- Uh, I need to look it up... the name...</i>

1752
01:06:34,820 --> 01:06:36,330
<i>I have to search for it.</i>

1753
01:06:36,330 --> 01:06:39,125
[Even he can't remember the name]
You don't remember the name? Where was it?

1754
01:06:39,125 --> 01:06:41,861
<i>Uh, you know... around Seongsan Ilchulbong.</i>

1755
01:06:41,861 --> 01:06:43,930
- Around Seongsan Ilchulbong.
<i>- Yes.</i>

1756
01:06:43,930 --> 01:06:46,265
You really don't remember the name?

1757
01:06:46,265 --> 01:06:49,963
<i>No, I need to look it up too, so the name...</i>

1758
01:06:49,963 --> 01:06:52,392
Ah, then please look it up right now,
Won Gi. Quickly.

1759
01:06:52,392 --> 01:06:53,456
<i>Yes, okay.</i>

1760
01:06:53,456 --> 01:06:55,061
- No, no... don't hang up.
- You can't hang up.

1761
01:06:55,061 --> 01:06:57,543
- Don't hang up. You can't hang up.
- 30 seconds left.

1762
01:06:57,543 --> 01:07:00,136
30 seconds left. 30 seconds.

1763
01:07:00,136 --> 01:07:01,280
<i>Okay.</i>

1764
01:07:01,280 --> 01:07:03,519
[As time slips away helplessly...]

1765
01:07:03,519 --> 01:07:05,586
[Lips going dry...]

1766
01:07:06,219 --> 01:07:08,488
[I'd rather not look]

1767
01:07:08,488 --> 01:07:09,859
[Please!]

1768
01:07:09,859 --> 01:07:11,311
[Extreme anxiety symptoms...]

1769
01:07:11,311 --> 01:07:12,948
Can you find it?

1770
01:07:13,826 --> 01:07:15,661
<i>- Just a second.</i>
- Okay.

1771
01:07:15,661 --> 01:07:18,231
[Ten-second countdown begins]
Ten, nine...

1772
01:07:18,231 --> 01:07:20,199
[Sigh]
eight...

1773
01:07:20,199 --> 01:07:22,291
seven, six...

1774
01:07:22,291 --> 01:07:25,338
[Will they hear the name in time?]
five, four, three...

1775
01:07:25,338 --> 01:07:27,836
<i>- The name here is...</i>
- Yeah.

1776
01:07:27,836 --> 01:07:30,977
- two, one.
<i>- That "top-quality black pork place."</i>

1777
01:07:30,977 --> 01:07:32,752
- "Top grade?"
- Hang up!

1778
01:07:32,752 --> 01:07:34,111
[Chance over]

1779
01:07:34,111 --> 01:07:37,320
Why are you being so loud?

1780
01:07:37,320 --> 01:07:39,905
Your voice was so loud we couldn't hear him.

1781
01:07:39,905 --> 01:07:41,749
[The room fills only with sighs...]
Top grade?

1782
01:07:41,749 --> 01:07:43,957
[Speechless]

1783
01:07:45,311 --> 01:07:49,485
- Did he say "ilgeun?"
- I think he said "ilgeum."

1784
01:07:49,485 --> 01:07:51,316
- Wasn't it "ilgeup?" Top grade?
- Ah, top grade?

1785
01:07:51,316 --> 01:07:53,156
"Ilgeum?"

1786
01:07:53,156 --> 01:07:55,666
[Not a single person heard it properly...]
"Jeil Top Grade Black Pork."

1787
01:07:55,666 --> 01:07:56,702
It might've been "top grade."

1788
01:07:56,702 --> 01:07:58,302
- Top grade.
- Top grade.

1789
01:07:58,302 --> 01:08:01,541
Let's just type "Seongsan Ilchulbong Jeil"
into the GPS for now.

1790
01:08:01,541 --> 01:08:03,333
Ah, right? That'll work.

1791
01:08:03,333 --> 01:08:05,711
- So something will come out, right?
- Then a bunch of results should come up.

1792
01:08:05,711 --> 01:08:08,628
And once we get close,
you'll remember the road.

1793
01:08:08,628 --> 01:08:09,619
Yeah, I remember the road.

1794
01:08:09,619 --> 01:08:11,050
Yeah, then let's head that way.

1795
01:08:11,050 --> 01:08:14,588
It really was right on the coastal road.

1796
01:08:14,588 --> 01:08:16,307
It's okay.

1797
01:08:16,307 --> 01:08:17,784
[Just the area and name are a big win]
I think we can find it.

1798
01:08:17,784 --> 01:08:19,494
- We can find it.
- We can find it.

1799
01:08:19,494 --> 01:08:21,794
We saw a poop truck today,
and stepped in poop too.

1800
01:08:21,794 --> 01:08:23,572
[Almost stepped in poop]

1801
01:08:23,572 --> 01:08:26,537
[Will their firmly believed
"2-poops-a-day" luck really happen?]

1802
01:08:26,537 --> 01:08:27,988
After answering the phone,

1803
01:08:27,988 --> 01:08:29,564
[What on earth is happening?]
he'll be completely clueless like this...

1804
01:08:29,564 --> 01:08:30,432
Won Gi!

1805
01:08:30,432 --> 01:08:33,026
[Won Gi! Thank you so much!]

1806
01:08:34,543 --> 01:08:35,852
Let's just drink it, guys.

1807
01:08:35,852 --> 01:08:38,168
[The staff suddenly gets hectic]
Then drive-thru near the airport?

1808
01:08:38,168 --> 01:08:40,746
Directors, would you like iced Americanos?

1809
01:08:40,746 --> 01:08:43,324
Are you torturing us with coffee right now?

1810
01:08:43,961 --> 01:08:46,922
[Weren't we supposed to be fate-bound?]
Ah, you can't drink it? Then...

1811
01:08:47,857 --> 01:08:49,622
- Iced tea or some iced...
- I'll have some coffee.

1812
01:08:49,622 --> 01:08:50,886
Oh, you're gonna drink coffee?

1813
01:08:50,886 --> 01:08:52,102
[Even with the director's
low caffeine tolerance...]

1814
01:08:52,102 --> 01:08:53,740
If you can't drink it, I'll drink it instead.

1815
01:08:53,740 --> 01:08:54,927
[Don't worry]

1816
01:08:55,760 --> 01:08:57,964
How much is one iced Americano?

1817
01:08:57,964 --> 01:09:00,722
How much is the small one?

1818
01:09:00,722 --> 01:09:02,100
[Why is he suddenly so interested?]

1819
01:09:02,100 --> 01:09:03,624
Probably the same.

1820
01:09:03,624 --> 01:09:06,824
[Suddenly counting the money
left in the wallet...]

1821
01:09:07,543 --> 01:09:09,236
135,000 won...

1822
01:09:09,236 --> 01:09:10,786
- 135,000 won.
- Yeah.

1823
01:09:11,460 --> 01:09:13,929
Then we'll just order one cup for us.

1824
01:09:14,747 --> 01:09:16,726
[Eye contact]
No.

1825
01:09:16,726 --> 01:09:19,584
[Ah... I'm not supposed to order it...]

1826
01:09:19,584 --> 01:09:22,120
[He quietly puts the money back...]

1827
01:09:22,120 --> 01:09:24,985
But I think I need a cup of coffee.
I'm so tired right now.

1828
01:09:24,985 --> 01:09:27,902
Let's grab a coffee! How about it?

1829
01:09:30,329 --> 01:09:31,501
[And nobody answered...]

1830
01:09:31,501 --> 01:09:33,086
Nobody's answering.

1831
01:09:33,086 --> 01:09:36,335
- How about we just sleep a little?
- Yeah, let's sleep.

1832
01:09:36,335 --> 01:09:39,274
[Who knew there was
such an economical solution...]

1833
01:09:39,274 --> 01:09:40,752
Let's sleep.

1834
01:09:40,752 --> 01:09:43,524
You sleep, I sleep too.

1835
01:09:44,136 --> 01:09:47,231
There's a strawberry milk
left for whoever's thirsty.

1836
01:09:47,231 --> 01:09:48,447
Wow...

1837
01:09:48,447 --> 01:09:50,899
[Wow... it's the perfect day for a nap...]

1838
01:09:50,899 --> 01:09:53,648
- Yumi, you don't usually drink coffee, right?
- I love coffee.

1839
01:09:53,648 --> 01:09:55,851
[So Yumi likes it too...]

1840
01:09:55,851 --> 01:09:57,781
I usually drink iced Americano
on an empty stomach.

1841
01:09:57,781 --> 01:09:59,380
[Holding back together for Jeju...]
Oh, really?

1842
01:10:00,177 --> 01:10:01,598
- I think they found it.
- Oh, you found it?

1843
01:10:01,598 --> 01:10:02,566
[Staff seems to have found
the black pork place]

1844
01:10:02,566 --> 01:10:03,840
You found it?

1845
01:10:03,840 --> 01:10:05,598
- Did y'all finally find it?
- The one by the beach?

1846
01:10:05,598 --> 01:10:07,165
[The information is limited,
so even the staff isn't sure]

1847
01:10:07,165 --> 01:10:09,798
If you search "V pork restaurant," it comes up.

1848
01:10:09,798 --> 01:10:10,874
- Tae Hyung.
- Did you go here?

1849
01:10:10,874 --> 01:10:13,130
- Yeah.
- The four of us went together.

1850
01:10:13,130 --> 01:10:17,350
I'm telling you, if you search
"V pork restaurant," it pops right up.

1851
01:10:17,350 --> 01:10:18,851
What did he say earlier again?

1852
01:10:18,851 --> 01:10:20,783
- Jeil Top Grade?
- Jeil Top Grade?

1853
01:10:20,783 --> 01:10:21,957
[Actually, the restaurant name
contains "gil," not "il"]

1854
01:10:21,957 --> 01:10:23,015
- Ilgeup?
- Jeil Ilgeum?

1855
01:10:23,015 --> 01:10:25,893
Then he mentioned Jeju,
but you told us to hang up.

1856
01:10:25,893 --> 01:10:28,183
Jeju black, black pork something.

1857
01:10:28,183 --> 01:10:31,983
Seriously though,
you should pay for half of this.

1858
01:10:31,983 --> 01:10:35,087
- Why?
- You were too loud. So we couldn't hear.

1859
01:10:35,087 --> 01:10:37,052
We could've heard it all in two seconds.

1860
01:10:37,052 --> 01:10:38,742
[An immediate group attack]

1861
01:10:38,742 --> 01:10:42,468
Four, five... three...

1862
01:10:42,468 --> 01:10:46,033
- Then should we bet coffee?
- A game?

1863
01:10:46,033 --> 01:10:47,473
Not exactly a game.

1864
01:10:47,473 --> 01:10:50,475
["Sorry About That" Corner,
by the loud production team]

1865
01:10:50,475 --> 01:10:52,770
You don't have your phones, right?

1866
01:10:52,770 --> 01:10:54,244
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1867
01:10:54,244 --> 01:10:58,133
If you guess the exact current time,
you get three coffees.

1868
01:10:58,133 --> 01:11:00,877
[Just match the hour and minute]
- Down to the minute. - Down to the minute?

1869
01:11:00,877 --> 01:11:02,321
But if it's within plus or minus

1870
01:11:02,321 --> 01:11:05,044
- five minutes, I'll give you just one drink.
- Five minutes?

1871
01:11:05,044 --> 01:11:08,830
[Guess the exact time, they get 3 coffees,
within ±5 minutes, they get 1 coffee]

1872
01:11:08,830 --> 01:11:12,447
Since time is still passing,
it's the exact moment you say it.

1873
01:11:12,447 --> 01:11:13,801
What time was our ferry again?

1874
01:11:13,801 --> 01:11:18,487
- Ours was at 3:00, and we boarded at 2:50 PM.
- But I think it's 3:30 PM right now.

1875
01:11:18,487 --> 01:11:19,878
3:25 PM!

1876
01:11:19,878 --> 01:11:22,658
No, no. It's past 25 minutes.

1877
01:11:23,328 --> 01:11:25,522
At least, it's definitely
in the 3 o'clock hour.

1878
01:11:26,245 --> 01:11:29,315
If it really left exactly at 3:00 PM,

1879
01:11:29,315 --> 01:11:31,070
then how much time has passed now?

1880
01:11:31,070 --> 01:11:33,655
About 30 minutes have passed.

1881
01:11:33,655 --> 01:11:35,379
- Has it really been 30 minutes?
- Yeah.

1882
01:11:35,379 --> 01:11:36,642
Yeah, I think so.

1883
01:11:36,642 --> 01:11:38,825
Wouldn't it be somewhere
between 35 and 40 minutes?

1884
01:11:38,825 --> 01:11:40,056
[Yumi &amp; Woo Shik are
both sure it's past 3:30]

1885
01:11:40,056 --> 01:11:43,839
So I think it's somewhere
between 3:30 and 3:45 PM.

1886
01:11:43,839 --> 01:11:46,412
Time's passing right now.
Another minute just passed.

1887
01:11:47,037 --> 01:11:50,370
Ah, 3:40 PM? 3:42 PM!

1888
01:11:51,245 --> 01:11:54,220
What about you? What time do you think it is?

1889
01:11:54,220 --> 01:11:56,742
I think maybe 3:35 PM?

1890
01:11:56,742 --> 01:11:59,009
- Then...
- Ah, wait, what time was our ferry again?

1891
01:11:59,009 --> 01:12:01,647
- 3 o'clock.
- It's the 3 o'clock ferry. Departure was at 3.

1892
01:12:01,647 --> 01:12:04,050
I feel like at most it'd be 3:35.

1893
01:12:04,050 --> 01:12:07,153
I'm saying 3:35, but anyway,
it's definitely past 30 minutes.

1894
01:12:07,153 --> 01:12:08,321
Hey, Siri!

1895
01:12:08,321 --> 01:12:10,457
[What a genius? Suddenly summoning AI...]

1896
01:12:10,457 --> 01:12:13,584
- Hey Siri, what time is it right now?
- Siri!

1897
01:12:13,584 --> 01:12:15,084
No, Sari, no!

1898
01:12:15,084 --> 01:12:17,797
[Let's just leave Siri alone]

1899
01:12:17,797 --> 01:12:21,235
[The deeper the discussion gets,
the more time passes...]

1900
01:12:21,235 --> 01:12:22,802
3:34 PM!

1901
01:12:22,802 --> 01:12:25,335
- Should we go with 3:35?
- Me too, 3:34 PM.

1902
01:12:25,335 --> 01:12:26,342
3:35 PM.

1903
01:12:26,342 --> 01:12:27,353
- 3:35 PM?
- 3:35 PM.

1904
01:12:27,353 --> 01:12:29,492
- Please say it clearly when you challenge.
- Let's go with 3:35 PM.

1905
01:12:29,492 --> 01:12:31,635
[They agree on 3:35 PM]
- 3:35 PM? - Yeah, 3:35 PM.

1906
01:12:31,635 --> 01:12:32,826
- Challenge!
- Challenge.

1907
01:12:32,826 --> 01:12:34,847
3:35 PM!

1908
01:12:34,847 --> 01:12:35,978
[Will they at least win one coffee?]

1909
01:12:35,978 --> 01:12:37,142
3:35 PM...

1910
01:12:37,142 --> 01:12:40,199
Current time, 3...

1911
01:12:40,925 --> 01:12:43,480
3:30...

1912
01:12:43,480 --> 01:12:46,080
[At least the 30 minutes are correct!]

1913
01:12:46,080 --> 01:12:47,530
[What will the last digit be?]

1914
01:12:47,530 --> 01:12:48,531
3:35.

1915
01:12:48,531 --> 01:12:49,786
- Really? Show me.
- Seriously?

1916
01:12:49,786 --> 01:12:52,468
[Current time: 3:35]

1917
01:12:55,968 --> 01:12:58,810
[Correct answer!]
Oh, what? What?

1918
01:12:58,810 --> 01:13:00,431
[They're flying high]
What? Seriously?

1919
01:13:00,431 --> 01:13:02,189
[Is this real?]

1920
01:13:02,189 --> 01:13:03,634
[They got it exactly right, no errors]
What?

1921
01:13:03,634 --> 01:13:06,900
I totally thought we'd just get one cup.
I was only expecting one.

1922
01:13:06,900 --> 01:13:09,806
[Even getting one cup would've been amazing...
how did this happen?]

1923
01:13:09,806 --> 01:13:11,921
They said you called it right at 3:35.

1924
01:13:11,921 --> 01:13:14,402
It was 3:32 when we first started.

1925
01:13:14,402 --> 01:13:17,728
I said it felt like 3:35, and then
another minute or two passed, right?

1926
01:13:17,728 --> 01:13:19,372
- Right.
- Exactly.

1927
01:13:19,372 --> 01:13:20,857
- Wow!
- Wow!

1928
01:13:20,857 --> 01:13:23,662
This is seriously giving me chills.

1929
01:13:23,662 --> 01:13:25,604
- Wow!
- This is insane.

1930
01:13:25,604 --> 01:13:27,304
[The excitement just won't fade...]

1931
01:13:27,304 --> 01:13:29,808
This is insane. Maybe today is our lucky day...
we even saw a poop truck!

1932
01:13:29,808 --> 01:13:31,606
We saw a poop truck earlier today.

1933
01:13:31,606 --> 01:13:34,057
[The "two poops a day" theory is proven]
- On the way here? - Yeah.

1934
01:13:34,057 --> 01:13:36,108
What do we do? Hurry, buy it for me!

1935
01:13:36,108 --> 01:13:38,085
- We'll take your orders now.
- Iced Americano!

1936
01:13:38,085 --> 01:13:40,092
[United by iced Americanos]
- Iced Americano. - Iced Americano.

1937
01:13:40,092 --> 01:13:41,285
[Celebration: They won three iced Americanos!]
Iced Americano.

1938
01:13:41,285 --> 01:13:45,170
I feel like I've been drowning
in dopamine since this morning.

1939
01:13:45,170 --> 01:13:47,659
I was honestly shocked
that we got it that right.

1940
01:13:47,659 --> 01:13:49,370
Since departure was at 3:00 PM,

1941
01:13:49,370 --> 01:13:52,794
I thought maybe not
that much time had passed yet.

1942
01:13:52,794 --> 01:13:55,250
Around 3:30 to 3:35?

1943
01:13:55,250 --> 01:13:57,433
And somehow we nailed it exactly, so...

1944
01:13:57,433 --> 01:14:00,582
I was seriously overflowing
with excitement then.

1945
01:14:00,582 --> 01:14:03,780
I think I literally jumped with my butt
while sitting down.

1946
01:14:03,780 --> 01:14:06,635
[That moment was basically a human spring]
While sitting down.

1947
01:14:06,635 --> 01:14:08,674
[It remained a strong memory for Woo Shik too]
Yeah.

1948
01:14:08,674 --> 01:14:12,661
Now that the three of us are together,
we think things through together.

1949
01:14:12,661 --> 01:14:16,591
So maybe that's why we were in sync.

1950
01:14:16,591 --> 01:14:18,917
Come to think of it,

1951
01:14:18,917 --> 01:14:21,962
that was the first time on this trip

1952
01:14:21,962 --> 01:14:25,299
that we each had a drink.

1953
01:14:25,299 --> 01:14:27,693
- You've shared drinks before.
- Yeah, always.

1954
01:14:27,693 --> 01:14:29,025
[The "one coffee per person" memory...]

1955
01:14:29,025 --> 01:14:30,627
- Oh, it's here.
- Wow, it's huge!

1956
01:14:30,627 --> 01:14:32,786
[The long-awaited caffeine recharge time!]

1957
01:14:32,786 --> 01:14:34,873
We can proudly drink this now. right?

1958
01:14:34,873 --> 01:14:36,762
You can totally drink this proudly.

1959
01:14:36,762 --> 01:14:38,947
Thank you!

1960
01:14:38,947 --> 01:14:41,298
[Luxury time with one coffee per person]
- Here you go. - Thank you!

1961
01:14:41,298 --> 01:14:43,776
[Starting with Woo Shik,
who almost chose sleep over coffee...]

1962
01:14:43,776 --> 01:14:45,835
[So good]

1963
01:14:45,835 --> 01:14:48,214
[Choi Woo Shik, no regrets]

1964
01:14:48,214 --> 01:14:49,352
Oh, thank you!

1965
01:14:49,352 --> 01:14:51,632
[Even Po-po, who loves
iced Americanos, takes a sip]

1966
01:14:51,632 --> 01:14:53,504
Wow!

1967
01:14:54,328 --> 01:14:56,492
[Gulp gulp]

1968
01:14:56,492 --> 01:15:00,037
I feel like this is the first time
I've properly had coffee on this trip.

1969
01:15:00,037 --> 01:15:02,085
We kept moving around nonstop.

1970
01:15:02,895 --> 01:15:05,698
I usually run on coffee,
but not so much this time.

1971
01:15:05,698 --> 01:15:09,035
[So every sip feels even more precious]

1972
01:15:09,035 --> 01:15:10,841
This is seriously good.

1973
01:15:11,716 --> 01:15:16,126
[No words needed]

1974
01:15:16,126 --> 01:15:19,545
[A tiny café on the sea where
everything feels perfect]

1975
01:15:19,545 --> 01:15:22,956
[And they get closer to Jeju]
- This is fun, right? - Yeah.

1976
01:15:22,956 --> 01:15:24,306
[Next week]

1977
01:15:24,306 --> 01:15:25,406
What was it called again?

1978
01:15:25,406 --> 01:15:27,834
[They need to find the black pork spot ASAP]
- This kind of place. - Yeah.

1979
01:15:27,834 --> 01:15:30,018
[It just won't come up]
- Nope, can't find it. - Ah, come on.

1980
01:15:30,018 --> 01:15:32,225
[Without knowing the name, they can't go there]
Darn it, this is getting rough.

1981
01:15:32,225 --> 01:15:33,575
Should we quickly go to a PC café?

1982
01:15:33,575 --> 01:15:34,910
If we search for "Kim Tae Hyung
black pork restaurant,"

1983
01:15:34,910 --> 01:15:36,313
- it'd come right up.
- It'd come right up.

1984
01:15:36,313 --> 01:15:38,314
- Then let's go to a PC café.
- If we go there, we'll find it right away.

1985
01:15:38,314 --> 01:15:39,664
[Running out of time, they look for a PC café]
We'll find it right away.

1986
01:15:39,664 --> 01:15:41,621
But this... I don't think it's open.

1987
01:15:41,621 --> 01:15:43,284
[They can't find a place that's open...]
It's closed. Over there.

1988
01:15:43,284 --> 01:15:44,895
Please let the PC café be open.

1989
01:15:44,895 --> 01:15:46,509
[Frustratingly, they can't find one]

1990
01:15:46,509 --> 01:15:48,278
[Eventually, desperate for black pork...]
Let's ask to borrow someone's phone.

1991
01:15:48,278 --> 01:15:51,016
[They resort to asking people directly]
Darn, how are we supposed to borrow one here?

1992
01:15:51,016 --> 01:15:52,434
Um, excuse me...

1993
01:15:52,434 --> 01:15:54,106
[Will they make it before closing?]

1994
01:15:54,106 --> 01:15:55,748
[And then...]

1995
01:15:55,748 --> 01:15:57,008
It gets this dark?

1996
01:15:57,008 --> 01:15:59,282
[Jeju suddenly went pitch black...]
I can't see anything. We are in Jeju, right?

1997
01:15:59,282 --> 01:16:00,871
Hey, we need to find a place to stay now.

1998
01:16:00,871 --> 01:16:02,503
Since we can't look anything up...

1999
01:16:02,503 --> 01:16:03,680
Should we just sleep in the car?

2000
01:16:03,680 --> 01:16:05,104
[Still nowhere to sleep at midnight]
At this hour, they're probably all closed.

2001
01:16:05,104 --> 01:16:06,349
Where are we actually supposed to sleep?

2002
01:16:06,349 --> 01:16:09,550
[Eventually...]
Yeah, let's just party until tomorrow morning.

2003
01:16:09,550 --> 01:16:11,504
We'll just hang out till six in the morning.

2004
01:16:11,504 --> 01:16:13,480
[So they stay up all night like true youths?]
Honestly, we weren't gonna sleep anyway.

2005
01:16:13,480 --> 01:16:16,535
[What will their final night look like?]
We can just sleep on the plane. I'm young.

2006
01:16:16,535 --> 01:16:18,428
[Last day of the trip]
We really traveled to our heart's content.

2007
01:16:18,428 --> 01:16:20,875
[Back to Seoul at last!]
- We finally made it. - Ah, this is emotional.

2008
01:16:20,875 --> 01:16:22,602
[But they still had one mission left]
It's an honor.

2009
01:16:22,602 --> 01:16:25,206
- Then let's sit in the same seats again.
- Yeah, okay.

2010
01:16:25,206 --> 01:16:27,592
[The safe return livestream!]
- You first, sit inside. - Should I go first?

2011
01:16:27,592 --> 01:16:30,194
- Hello.
- Ah, our proud Unplanned Trip crew.

2012
01:16:30,194 --> 01:16:32,922
- Do we smell?
- Is it okay if we open this?

2013
01:16:32,922 --> 01:16:35,328
[Oh my stomach]

2014
01:16:35,328 --> 01:16:38,030
[The full vivid story coming soon]
I'm always the only one talking.

2015
01:16:38,030 --> 01:16:41,732
I can't go into details,
but it's due to transportation issues.

2016
01:16:43,224 --> 01:16:45,218
No, but even so, during a livestream...

2017
01:16:45,218 --> 01:16:47,006
No, I was smiling like this.

2018
01:16:47,006 --> 01:16:49,016
But yawning like that...

2019
01:16:49,016 --> 01:16:52,133
I kind of have a habit of smiling
with my mouth closed.

2020
01:16:52,133 --> 01:16:54,513
[Congratulations on the safe return]
Sorry, I'll smile with my mouth open.
